97typedef HashMap<const RenderBlock*, std::unique_ptr<TrackedRendererListHashSet>> TrackedDescendantsMap;
98typedef HashMap<const RenderBox*, std::unique_ptr<HashSet<const RenderBlock*>>> TrackedContainerMap;
99
100static TrackedDescendantsMap* percentHeightDescendantsMap;
101static TrackedContainerMap* percentHeightContainerMap;
102
103static void insertIntoTrackedRendererMaps(const RenderBlock& container, RenderBox& descendant)
104{
105 if (!percentHeightDescendantsMap) {
106 percentHeightDescendantsMap = new TrackedDescendantsMap;
107 percentHeightContainerMap = new TrackedContainerMap;
108 }
109
110 auto& descendantSet = percentHeightDescendantsMap->ensure(&container, [] {
111 return makeUnique<TrackedRendererListHashSet>();
112 }).iterator->value;
113
114 bool added = descendantSet->add(&descendant).isNewEntry;
115 if (!added) {
116 ASSERT(percentHeightContainerMap->get(&descendant));
117 ASSERT(percentHeightContainerMap->get(&descendant)->contains(&container));
118 return;
119 }
120
121 auto& containerSet = percentHeightContainerMap->ensure(&descendant, [] {
122 return makeUnique<HashSet<const RenderBlock*>>();
123 }).iterator->value;
124
125 ASSERT(!containerSet->contains(&container));
126 containerSet->add(&container);
127}
128
129static void removeFromTrackedRendererMaps(RenderBox& descendant)
130{
131 if (!percentHeightDescendantsMap)
132 return;
133
134 std::unique_ptr<HashSet<const RenderBlock*>> containerSet = percentHeightContainerMap->take(&descendant);
135 if (!containerSet)
136 return;
137
138 for (auto* container : *containerSet) {
139 // FIXME: Disabling this assert temporarily until we fix the layout
140 // bugs associated with positioned objects not properly cleared from
141 // their ancestor chain before being moved. See webkit bug 93766.
142 // ASSERT(descendant->isDescendantOf(container));
143 auto descendantsMapIterator = percentHeightDescendantsMap->find(container);
144 ASSERT(descendantsMapIterator != percentHeightDescendantsMap->end());
145 if (descendantsMapIterator == percentHeightDescendantsMap->end())
146 continue;
147 auto& descendantSet = descendantsMapIterator->value;
148 ASSERT(descendantSet->contains(&descendant));
149 descendantSet->remove(&descendant);
150 if (descendantSet->isEmpty())
151 percentHeightDescendantsMap->remove(descendantsMapIterator);
152 }
153}
154
155class PositionedDescendantsMap {
156public:
157 enum class MoveDescendantToEnd { No, Yes };
158 void addDescendant(const RenderBlock& containingBlock, RenderBox& positionedDescendant, MoveDescendantToEnd moveDescendantToEnd)
159 {
160 // Protect against double insert where a descendant would end up with multiple containing blocks.
161 auto* previousContainingBlock = m_containerMap.get(&positionedDescendant);
162 if (previousContainingBlock && previousContainingBlock != &containingBlock) {
163 if (auto* descendants = m_descendantsMap.get(previousContainingBlock))
164 descendants->remove(&positionedDescendant);
165 }
166
167 auto& descendants = m_descendantsMap.ensure(&containingBlock, [] {
168 return makeUnique<TrackedRendererListHashSet>();
169 }).iterator->value;
170
171 bool isNewEntry = moveDescendantToEnd == MoveDescendantToEnd::Yes ? descendants->appendOrMoveToLast(&positionedDescendant).isNewEntry
172 : descendants->add(&positionedDescendant).isNewEntry;
173 if (!isNewEntry) {
174 ASSERT(m_containerMap.contains(&positionedDescendant));
175 return;
176 }
177 m_containerMap.set(&positionedDescendant, &containingBlock);
178 }
179
180 void removeDescendant(const RenderBox& positionedDescendant)
181 {
182 auto* containingBlock = m_containerMap.take(&positionedDescendant);
183 if (!containingBlock)
184 return;
185
186 auto descendantsIterator = m_descendantsMap.find(containingBlock);
187 ASSERT(descendantsIterator != m_descendantsMap.end());
188 if (descendantsIterator == m_descendantsMap.end())
189 return;
190
191 auto& descendants = descendantsIterator->value;
192 ASSERT(descendants->contains(const_cast<RenderBox*>(&positionedDescendant)));
193
194 descendants->remove(const_cast<RenderBox*>(&positionedDescendant));
195 if (descendants->isEmpty())
196 m_descendantsMap.remove(descendantsIterator);
197 }
198
199 void removeContainingBlock(const RenderBlock& containingBlock)
200 {
201 auto descendants = m_descendantsMap.take(&containingBlock);
202 if (!descendants)
203 return;
204
205 for (auto* renderer : *descendants)
206 m_containerMap.remove(renderer);
207 }
208
209 TrackedRendererListHashSet* positionedRenderers(const RenderBlock& containingBlock) const
210 {
211 return m_descendantsMap.get(&containingBlock);
212 }
213
214private:
215 using DescendantsMap = HashMap<const RenderBlock*, std::unique_ptr<TrackedRendererListHashSet>>;
216 using ContainerMap = HashMap<const RenderBox*, const RenderBlock*>;
217
218 DescendantsMap m_descendantsMap;
219 ContainerMap m_containerMap;
220};
221
222static PositionedDescendantsMap& positionedDescendantsMap()
223{
224 static NeverDestroyed<PositionedDescendantsMap> mapForPositionedDescendants;
225 return mapForPositionedDescendants;
226}

268// This class helps dispatching the 'overflow' event on layout change. overflow can be set on RenderBoxes, yet the existing code
269// only works on RenderBlocks. If this change, this class should be shared with other RenderBoxes.
270class OverflowEventDispatcher {
271 WTF_MAKE_NONCOPYABLE(OverflowEventDispatcher);
272public:
273 OverflowEventDispatcher(const RenderBlock* block)
274 : m_block(block)
275 , m_hadHorizontalLayoutOverflow(false)
276 , m_hadVerticalLayoutOverflow(false)
277 {
278 m_shouldDispatchEvent = !m_block->isAnonymous() && m_block->hasOverflowClip() && m_block->document().hasListenerType(Document::OVERFLOWCHANGED_LISTENER);
279 if (m_shouldDispatchEvent) {
280 m_hadHorizontalLayoutOverflow = m_block->hasHorizontalLayoutOverflow();
281 m_hadVerticalLayoutOverflow = m_block->hasVerticalLayoutOverflow();
282 }
283 }
284
285 ~OverflowEventDispatcher()
286 {
287 if (!m_shouldDispatchEvent)
288 return;
289
290 bool hasHorizontalLayoutOverflow = m_block->hasHorizontalLayoutOverflow();
291 bool hasVerticalLayoutOverflow = m_block->hasVerticalLayoutOverflow();
292
293 bool horizontalLayoutOverflowChanged = hasHorizontalLayoutOverflow != m_hadHorizontalLayoutOverflow;
294 bool verticalLayoutOverflowChanged = hasVerticalLayoutOverflow != m_hadVerticalLayoutOverflow;
295 if (!horizontalLayoutOverflowChanged && !verticalLayoutOverflowChanged)
296 return;
297
298 Ref<OverflowEvent> overflowEvent = OverflowEvent::create(horizontalLayoutOverflowChanged, hasHorizontalLayoutOverflow, verticalLayoutOverflowChanged, hasVerticalLayoutOverflow);
299 overflowEvent->setTarget(m_block->element());
300 m_block->document().enqueueOverflowEvent(WTFMove(overflowEvent));
301 }
302
303private:
304 const RenderBlock* m_block;
305 bool m_shouldDispatchEvent;
306 bool m_hadHorizontalLayoutOverflow;
307 bool m_hadVerticalLayoutOverflow;
308};

320static void removeBlockFromPercentageDescendantAndContainerMaps(RenderBlock* block)
321{
322 if (!percentHeightDescendantsMap)
323 return;
324 std::unique_ptr<TrackedRendererListHashSet> descendantSet = percentHeightDescendantsMap->take(block);
325 if (!descendantSet)
326 return;
327
328 for (auto* descendant : *descendantSet) {
329 auto it = percentHeightContainerMap->find(descendant);
330 ASSERT(it != percentHeightContainerMap->end());
331 if (it == percentHeightContainerMap->end())
332 continue;
333 auto* containerSet = it->value.get();
334 ASSERT(containerSet->contains(block));
335 containerSet->remove(block);
336 if (containerSet->isEmpty())
337 percentHeightContainerMap->remove(it);
338 }
339}

348}

350// Note that this is not called for RenderBlockFlows.
351void RenderBlock::willBeDestroyed()
352{
353 if (!renderTreeBeingDestroyed()) {
354 if (parent())
355 parent()->dirtyLinesFromChangedChild(*this);
356 }
357
358 blockWillBeDestroyed();
359
360 RenderBox::willBeDestroyed();
361}

363void RenderBlock::blockWillBeDestroyed()
364{
365 removeFromUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
366
367 removeBlockFromPercentageDescendantAndContainerMaps(this);
368 positionedDescendantsMap().removeContainingBlock(*this);
369}

376void RenderBlock::removePositionedObjectsIfNeeded(const RenderStyle& oldStyle, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
377{
378 bool hadTransform = oldStyle.hasTransformRelatedProperty();
379 bool willHaveTransform = newStyle.hasTransformRelatedProperty();
380 if (oldStyle.position() == newStyle.position() && hadTransform == willHaveTransform)
381 return;
382
383 // We are no longer the containing block for out-of-flow descendants.
384 bool outOfFlowDescendantsHaveNewContainingBlock = (hadTransform && !willHaveTransform) || (newStyle.position() == PositionType::Static && !willHaveTransform);
385 if (outOfFlowDescendantsHaveNewContainingBlock) {
386 // Our out-of-flow descendants will be inserted into a new containing block's positioned objects list during the next layout.
387 removePositionedObjects(nullptr, NewContainingBlock);
388 return;
389 }
390
391 // We are a new containing block.
392 if (oldStyle.position() == PositionType::Static && !hadTransform) {
393 // Remove our absolutely positioned descendants from their current containing block.
394 // They will be inserted into our positioned objects list during layout.
395 auto* containingBlock = parent();
396 while (containingBlock && !is<RenderView>(*containingBlock)
397 && (containingBlock->style().position() == PositionType::Static || (containingBlock->isInline() && !containingBlock->isReplaced()))) {
398 if (containingBlock->style().position() == PositionType::Relative && containingBlock->isInline() && !containingBlock->isReplaced()) {
399 containingBlock = containingBlock->containingBlock();
400 break;
401 }
402 containingBlock = containingBlock->parent();
403 }
404 if (containingBlock && is<RenderBlock>(*containingBlock))
405 downcast<RenderBlock>(*containingBlock).removePositionedObjects(this, NewContainingBlock);
406 }
407}

409void RenderBlock::styleWillChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
410{
411 const RenderStyle* oldStyle = hasInitializedStyle() ? &style() : nullptr;
412 setReplaced(newStyle.isDisplayInlineType());
413 if (oldStyle)
414 removePositionedObjectsIfNeeded(*oldStyle, newStyle);
415 RenderBox::styleWillChange(diff, newStyle);
416}
417
418static bool borderOrPaddingLogicalWidthChanged(const RenderStyle& oldStyle, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
419{
420 if (newStyle.isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
421 return oldStyle.borderLeftWidth() != newStyle.borderLeftWidth()
422 || oldStyle.borderRightWidth() != newStyle.borderRightWidth()
423 || oldStyle.paddingLeft() != newStyle.paddingLeft()
424 || oldStyle.paddingRight() != newStyle.paddingRight();
425 }
426
427 return oldStyle.borderTopWidth() != newStyle.borderTopWidth()
428 || oldStyle.borderBottomWidth() != newStyle.borderBottomWidth()
429 || oldStyle.paddingTop() != newStyle.paddingTop()
430 || oldStyle.paddingBottom() != newStyle.paddingBottom();
431}
432
433void RenderBlock::styleDidChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
434{
435 bool hadTransform = hasTransform();
436 RenderBox::styleDidChange(diff, oldStyle);
437
438 if (hadTransform != hasTransform())
439 adjustFragmentedFlowStateOnContainingBlockChangeIfNeeded();
440
441 propagateStyleToAnonymousChildren(PropagateToBlockChildrenOnly);
442
443 // It's possible for our border/padding to change, but for the overall logical width of the block to
444 // end up being the same. We keep track of this change so in layoutBlock, we can know to set relayoutChildren=true.
445 setShouldForceRelayoutChildren(oldStyle && diff == StyleDifference::Layout && needsLayout() && borderOrPaddingLogicalWidthChanged(*oldStyle, style()));
446}

448RenderPtr<RenderBlock> RenderBlock::clone() const
449{
450 RenderPtr<RenderBlock> cloneBlock;
451 if (isAnonymousBlock()) {
452 cloneBlock = RenderPtr<RenderBlock>(createAnonymousBlock());
453 cloneBlock->setChildrenInline(childrenInline());
454 } else {
455 RenderTreePosition insertionPosition(*parent());
456 cloneBlock = static_pointer_cast<RenderBlock>(element()->createElementRenderer(RenderStyle::clone(style()), insertionPosition));
457 cloneBlock->initializeStyle();
458
459 // This takes care of setting the right value of childrenInline in case
460 // generated content is added to cloneBlock and 'this' does not have
461 // generated content added yet.
462 cloneBlock->setChildrenInline(cloneBlock->firstChild() ? cloneBlock->firstChild()->isInline() : childrenInline());
463 }
464 cloneBlock->setFragmentedFlowState(fragmentedFlowState());
465 return cloneBlock;
466}

474bool RenderBlock::childrenPreventSelfCollapsing() const
475{
476 // Whether or not we collapse is dependent on whether all our normal flow children
477 // are also self-collapsing.
478 for (RenderBox* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
479 if (child->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
480 continue;
481 if (!child->isSelfCollapsingBlock())
482 return true;
483 }
484 return false;
485}
486
487bool RenderBlock::isSelfCollapsingBlock() const
488{
489 // We are not self-collapsing if we
490 // (a) have a non-zero height according to layout (an optimization to avoid wasting time)
491 // (b) are a table,
492 // (c) have border/padding,
493 // (d) have a min-height
494 // (e) have specified that one of our margins can't collapse using a CSS extension
495 if (logicalHeight() > 0
496 || isTable() || borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight()
497 || style().logicalMinHeight().isPositive()
498 || style().marginBeforeCollapse() == MarginCollapse::Separate || style().marginAfterCollapse() == MarginCollapse::Separate)
499 return false;
500
501 Length logicalHeightLength = style().logicalHeight();
502 bool hasAutoHeight = logicalHeightLength.isAuto();
503 if (logicalHeightLength.isPercentOrCalculated() && !document().inQuirksMode()) {
504 hasAutoHeight = true;
505 for (RenderBlock* cb = containingBlock(); cb && !is<RenderView>(*cb); cb = cb->containingBlock()) {
506 if (cb->style().logicalHeight().isFixed() || cb->isTableCell())
507 hasAutoHeight = false;
508 }
509 }
510
511 // If the height is 0 or auto, then whether or not we are a self-collapsing block depends
512 // on whether we have content that is all self-collapsing or not.
513 if (hasAutoHeight || ((logicalHeightLength.isFixed() || logicalHeightLength.isPercentOrCalculated()) && logicalHeightLength.isZero()))
514 return !childrenPreventSelfCollapsing();
515
516 return false;
517}

519static inline UpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction* currentUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction()
520{
521 if (!updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack())
522 return nullptr;
523 return &updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack()->last();
524}
525
526void RenderBlock::beginUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction()
527{
528 if (!updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack())
529 updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack() = makeUnique<DelayedUpdateScrollInfoStack>();
530 if (updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack()->isEmpty() || currentUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction()->view != &view())
531 updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack()->append(UpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction(view()));
532 ++currentUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction()->nestedCount;
533}
534
535void RenderBlock::endAndCommitUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction()
536{
537 UpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction* transaction = currentUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
538 ASSERT(transaction);
539 ASSERT(transaction->view == &view());
540 if (--transaction->nestedCount)
541 return;
542
543 // Calling RenderLayer::updateScrollInfoAfterLayout() may cause its associated block to layout again and
544 // updates its scroll info (i.e. call RenderBlock::updateScrollInfoAfterLayout()). We remove |transaction|
545 // from the transaction stack to ensure that all subsequent calls to RenderBlock::updateScrollInfoAfterLayout()
546 // are dispatched immediately. That is, to ensure that such subsequent calls aren't added to |transaction|
547 // while we are processing it.
548 auto blocksToUpdate = copyToVector(transaction->blocks);
549 updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack()->removeLast();
550 if (updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack()->isEmpty())
551 updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack() = nullptr;
552
553 for (auto* block : blocksToUpdate) {
554 ASSERT(block->hasOverflowClip());
555 block->layer()->updateScrollInfoAfterLayout();
556 }
557}
558
559void RenderBlock::removeFromUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction()
560{
561 if (UNLIKELY(updateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransactionStack().get() != 0)) {
562 UpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction* transaction = currentUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
563 ASSERT(transaction);
564 if (transaction->view == &view())
565 transaction->blocks.remove(this);
566 }
567}
568
569void RenderBlock::updateScrollInfoAfterLayout()
570{
571 if (!hasOverflowClip())
572 return;
573
574 // FIXME: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=97937
575 // Workaround for now. We cannot delay the scroll info for overflow
576 // for items with opposite writing directions, as the contents needs
577 // to overflow in that direction
578 if (!style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode()) {
579 UpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction* transaction = currentUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
580 if (transaction && transaction->view == &view()) {
581 transaction->blocks.add(this);
582 return;
583 }
584 }
585 if (layer())
586 layer()->updateScrollInfoAfterLayout();
587}
588
589void RenderBlock::layout()
590{
591 StackStats::LayoutCheckPoint layoutCheckPoint;
592 OverflowEventDispatcher dispatcher(this);
593
594 // Table cells call layoutBlock directly, so don't add any logic here. Put code into
595 // layoutBlock().
596 layoutBlock(false);
597
598 // It's safe to check for control clip here, since controls can never be table cells.
599 // If we have a lightweight clip, there can never be any overflow from children.
600 UpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction* transaction = currentUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
601 bool isDelayingUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutInView = transaction && transaction->view == &view();
602 if (hasControlClip() && m_overflow && !isDelayingUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutInView)
603 clearLayoutOverflow();
604
605 invalidateBackgroundObscurationStatus();
606}

632static bool shouldRecalculateMinMaxWidthsAffectedByAncestor(const RenderBox* box)
633{
634 // If the preferred widths are already dirty at this point (during layout), it actually means that we never need to calculate them, since that should
635 // have been carried out by an ancestor that's sized based on preferred widths (a shrink-to-fit container, for instance). In such cases the
636 // object will be left as dirty indefinitely, and it would just be a waste of time to calculate the preferred withs when nobody needs them.
637 if (box->preferredLogicalWidthsDirty())
638 return false;
639 // If our containing block also has min/max widths that are affected by the ancestry, we have already dealt with this object as well. Avoid
640 // unnecessary work and O(n^2) time complexity.
641 if (const RenderBox* cb = box->containingBlock()) {
642 if (cb->needsPreferredWidthsRecalculation() && !cb->preferredLogicalWidthsDirty())
643 return false;
644 }
645 return true;
646}
647
648bool RenderBlock::recomputeLogicalWidth()
649{
650 LayoutUnit oldWidth = logicalWidth();
651
652 // Laying out this object means that its containing block is also being laid out. This object is special, in that its min/max widths depend on
653 // the ancestry (min/max width calculation should ideally be strictly bottom-up, but that's not always the case), so since the containing
654 // block size may have changed, we need to recalculate the min/max widths of this object, and every child that has the same issue, recursively.
655 if (needsPreferredWidthsRecalculation() && shouldRecalculateMinMaxWidthsAffectedByAncestor(this))
656 setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(true, MarkOnlyThis);
657 updateLogicalWidth();
658
659 bool hasBorderOrPaddingLogicalWidthChanged = this->hasBorderOrPaddingLogicalWidthChanged();
660 setShouldForceRelayoutChildren(false);
661
662 return oldWidth != logicalWidth() || hasBorderOrPaddingLogicalWidthChanged;
663}

669}
670
671void RenderBlock::addOverflowFromChildren()
672{
673 if (childrenInline())
674 addOverflowFromInlineChildren();
675 else
676 addOverflowFromBlockChildren();
677
678 // If this block is flowed inside a flow thread, make sure its overflow is propagated to the containing fragments.
679 if (m_overflow) {
680 if (RenderFragmentedFlow* containingFragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow())
681 containingFragmentedFlow->addFragmentsVisualOverflow(this, m_overflow->visualOverflowRect());
682 }
683}
684
685// Overflow is always relative to the border-box of the element in question.
686// Therefore, if the element has a vertical scrollbar placed on the left, an overflow rect at x=2px would conceptually intersect the scrollbar.
687void RenderBlock::computeOverflow(LayoutUnit oldClientAfterEdge, bool)
688{
689 clearOverflow();
690 addOverflowFromChildren();
691
692 addOverflowFromPositionedObjects();
693
694 if (hasOverflowClip()) {
695 // When we have overflow clip, propagate the original spillout since it will include collapsed bottom margins
696 // and bottom padding. Set the axis we don't care about to be 1, since we want this overflow to always
697 // be considered reachable.
698 LayoutRect clientRect(flippedClientBoxRect());
699 LayoutRect rectToApply;
700 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
701 rectToApply = LayoutRect(clientRect.x(), clientRect.y(), 1_lu, std::max(0_lu, oldClientAfterEdge - clientRect.y()));
702 else
703 rectToApply = LayoutRect(clientRect.x(), clientRect.y(), std::max(0_lu, oldClientAfterEdge - clientRect.x()), 1_lu);
704 addLayoutOverflow(rectToApply);
705 if (hasRenderOverflow())
706 m_overflow->setLayoutClientAfterEdge(oldClientAfterEdge);
707 }
708
709 // Add visual overflow from box-shadow, border-image-outset and outline.
710 addVisualEffectOverflow();
711
712 // Add visual overflow from theme.
713 addVisualOverflowFromTheme();
714}
715
716void RenderBlock::clearLayoutOverflow()
717{
718 if (!m_overflow)
719 return;
720
721 if (visualOverflowRect() == borderBoxRect()) {
722 // FIXME: Implement complete solution for fragments overflow.
723 clearOverflow();
724 return;
725 }
726
727 m_overflow->setLayoutOverflow(borderBoxRect());
728}
729
730void RenderBlock::addOverflowFromBlockChildren()
731{
732 for (auto* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
733 if (!child->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
734 addOverflowFromChild(child);
735 }
736}
737
738void RenderBlock::addOverflowFromPositionedObjects()
739{
740 TrackedRendererListHashSet* positionedDescendants = positionedObjects();
741 if (!positionedDescendants)
742 return;
743
744 for (auto it = positionedDescendants->begin(), end = positionedDescendants->end(); it != end; ++it) {
745 RenderBox* positionedObject = *it;
746
747 // Fixed positioned elements don't contribute to layout overflow, since they don't scroll with the content.
748 if (positionedObject->style().position() != PositionType::Fixed)
749 addOverflowFromChild(positionedObject, { positionedObject->x(), positionedObject->y() });
750 }
751}
752
753void RenderBlock::addVisualOverflowFromTheme()
754{
755 if (!style().hasAppearance())
756 return;
757
758 FloatRect inflatedRect = borderBoxRect();
759 theme().adjustRepaintRect(*this, inflatedRect);
760 addVisualOverflow(snappedIntRect(LayoutRect(inflatedRect)));
761
762 if (RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow())
763 fragmentedFlow->addFragmentsVisualOverflowFromTheme(this);
764}
765
766LayoutUnit RenderBlock::computeStartPositionDeltaForChildAvoidingFloats(const RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit childMarginStart, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment)
767{
768 LayoutUnit startPosition = startOffsetForContent(fragment);
769
770 // Add in our start margin.
771 LayoutUnit oldPosition = startPosition + childMarginStart;
772 LayoutUnit newPosition = oldPosition;
773
774 LayoutUnit blockOffset = logicalTopForChild(child);
775 if (fragment)
776 blockOffset = std::max(blockOffset, blockOffset + (fragment->logicalTopForFragmentedFlowContent() - offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage()));
777
778 LayoutUnit startOff = startOffsetForLineInFragment(blockOffset, DoNotIndentText, fragment, logicalHeightForChild(child));
779
780 if (style().textAlign() != TextAlignMode::WebKitCenter && !child.style().marginStartUsing(&style()).isAuto()) {
781 if (childMarginStart < 0)
782 startOff += childMarginStart;
783 newPosition = std::max(newPosition, startOff); // Let the float sit in the child's margin if it can fit.
784 } else if (startOff != startPosition)
785 newPosition = startOff + childMarginStart;
786
787 return newPosition - oldPosition;
788}
789
790void RenderBlock::setLogicalLeftForChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit logicalLeft, ApplyLayoutDeltaMode applyDelta)
791{
792 if (isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
793 if (applyDelta == ApplyLayoutDelta)
794 view().frameView().layoutContext().addLayoutDelta(LayoutSize(child.x() - logicalLeft, 0_lu));
795 child.setX(logicalLeft);
796 } else {
797 if (applyDelta == ApplyLayoutDelta)
798 view().frameView().layoutContext().addLayoutDelta(LayoutSize(0_lu, child.y() - logicalLeft));
799 child.setY(logicalLeft);
800 }
801}
802
803void RenderBlock::setLogicalTopForChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit logicalTop, ApplyLayoutDeltaMode applyDelta)
804{
805 if (isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
806 if (applyDelta == ApplyLayoutDelta)
807 view().frameView().layoutContext().addLayoutDelta(LayoutSize(0_lu, child.y() - logicalTop));
808 child.setY(logicalTop);
809 } else {
810 if (applyDelta == ApplyLayoutDelta)
811 view().frameView().layoutContext().addLayoutDelta(LayoutSize(child.x() - logicalTop, 0_lu));
812 child.setX(logicalTop);
813 }
814}
815
816void RenderBlock::updateBlockChildDirtyBitsBeforeLayout(bool relayoutChildren, RenderBox& child)
817{
818 if (child.isOutOfFlowPositioned())
819 return;
820
821 // FIXME: Technically percentage height objects only need a relayout if their percentage isn't going to be turned into
822 // an auto value. Add a method to determine this, so that we can avoid the relayout.
823 if (relayoutChildren || (child.hasRelativeLogicalHeight() && !isRenderView()))
824 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
825
826 // If relayoutChildren is set and the child has percentage padding or an embedded content box, we also need to invalidate the childs pref widths.
827 if (relayoutChildren && child.needsPreferredWidthsRecalculation())
828 child.setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(true, MarkOnlyThis);
829}
830
831void RenderBlock::dirtyForLayoutFromPercentageHeightDescendants()
832{
833 if (!percentHeightDescendantsMap)
834 return;
835
836 TrackedRendererListHashSet* descendants = percentHeightDescendantsMap->get(this);
837 if (!descendants)
838 return;
839
840 for (auto it = descendants->begin(), end = descendants->end(); it != end; ++it) {
841 RenderElement* renderer = *it;
842 // Let's not dirty the height perecentage descendant when it has an absolutely positioned containing block ancestor. We should be able to dirty such boxes through the regular invalidation logic.
843 bool descendantNeedsLayout = true;
844 for (auto* ancestor = renderer->containingBlock(); ancestor && ancestor != this; ancestor = ancestor->containingBlock()) {
845 if (ancestor->isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
846 descendantNeedsLayout = false;
847 break;
848 }
849 }
850 if (!descendantNeedsLayout)
851 continue;
852
853 while (renderer != this) {
854 if (renderer->normalChildNeedsLayout())
855 break;
856 renderer->setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
857
858 // If the width of an image is affected by the height of a child (e.g., an image with an aspect ratio),
859 // then we have to dirty preferred widths, since even enclosing blocks can become dirty as a result.
860 // (A horizontal flexbox that contains an inline image wrapped in an anonymous block for example.)
861 if (renderer->hasIntrinsicAspectRatio() || renderer->style().hasAspectRatio())
862 renderer->setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(true);
863 auto* container = renderer->container();
864 // Mark the svg ancestor chain dirty as we walk to the container.
865 if (is<SVGElement>(renderer->element()) && container != renderer->parent()) {
866 auto* ancestor = renderer->parent();
867 ASSERT(ancestor->isDescendantOf(container));
868 while (ancestor != container) {
869 ancestor->setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
870 // This is the topmost SVG root, no need to go any further.
871 if (is<SVGSVGElement>(ancestor->element()) && !downcast<SVGSVGElement>(*ancestor->element()).ownerSVGElement())
872 break;
873 ancestor = ancestor->parent();
874 }
875 }
876 renderer = container;
877 ASSERT(renderer);
878 if (!renderer)
879 break;
880 }
881 }
882}
883
884void RenderBlock::simplifiedNormalFlowLayout()
885{
886 if (childrenInline()) {
887 ListHashSet<LegacyRootInlineBox*> lineBoxes;
888 for (InlineWalker walker(*this); !walker.atEnd(); walker.advance()) {
889 RenderObject& renderer = *walker.current();
890 if (!renderer.isOutOfFlowPositioned() && (renderer.isReplaced() || renderer.isFloating())) {
891 RenderBox& box = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer);
892 box.layoutIfNeeded();
893 if (box.inlineBoxWrapper())
894 lineBoxes.add(&box.inlineBoxWrapper()->root());
895 } else if (is<RenderText>(renderer) || (is<RenderInline>(renderer) && !walker.atEndOfInline()))
896 renderer.clearNeedsLayout();
897 }
898
899 // FIXME: Glyph overflow will get lost in this case, but not really a big deal.
900 // FIXME: Find a way to invalidate the knownToHaveNoOverflow flag on the InlineBoxes.
901 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap textBoxDataMap;
902 for (auto it = lineBoxes.begin(), end = lineBoxes.end(); it != end; ++it) {
903 LegacyRootInlineBox* box = *it;
904 box->computeOverflow(box->lineTop(), box->lineBottom(), textBoxDataMap);
905 }
906 } else {
907 for (auto* box = firstChildBox(); box; box = box->nextSiblingBox()) {
908 if (!box->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
909 box->layoutIfNeeded();
910 }
911 }
912}
913
914bool RenderBlock::canPerformSimplifiedLayout() const
915{
916 return (posChildNeedsLayout() || needsSimplifiedNormalFlowLayout()) && !normalChildNeedsLayout() && !selfNeedsLayout();
917}
918
919bool RenderBlock::simplifiedLayout()
920{
921 if (!canPerformSimplifiedLayout())
922 return false;
923
924 LayoutStateMaintainer statePusher(*this, locationOffset(), hasTransform() || hasReflection() || style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode());
925 if (needsPositionedMovementLayout() && !tryLayoutDoingPositionedMovementOnly())
926 return false;
927
928 // Lay out positioned descendants or objects that just need to recompute overflow.
929 if (needsSimplifiedNormalFlowLayout())
930 simplifiedNormalFlowLayout();
931
932 // Make sure a forced break is applied after the content if we are a flow thread in a simplified layout.
933 // This ensures the size information is correctly computed for the last auto-height fragment receiving content.
934 if (is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this))
935 downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this).applyBreakAfterContent(clientLogicalBottom());
936
937 // Lay out our positioned objects if our positioned child bit is set.
938 // Also, if an absolute position element inside a relative positioned container moves, and the absolute element has a fixed position
939 // child, neither the fixed element nor its container learn of the movement since posChildNeedsLayout() is only marked as far as the
940 // relative positioned container. So if we can have fixed pos objects in our positioned objects list check if any of them
941 // are statically positioned and thus need to move with their absolute ancestors.
942 bool canContainFixedPosObjects = canContainFixedPositionObjects();
943 if (posChildNeedsLayout() || canContainFixedPosObjects)
944 layoutPositionedObjects(false, !posChildNeedsLayout() && canContainFixedPosObjects);
945
946 // Recompute our overflow information.
947 // FIXME: We could do better here by computing a temporary overflow object from layoutPositionedObjects and only
948 // updating our overflow if we either used to have overflow or if the new temporary object has overflow.
949 // For now just always recompute overflow. This is no worse performance-wise than the old code that called rightmostPosition and
950 // lowestPosition on every relayout so it's not a regression.
951 // computeOverflow expects the bottom edge before we clamp our height. Since this information isn't available during
952 // simplifiedLayout, we cache the value in m_overflow.
953 LayoutUnit oldClientAfterEdge = hasRenderOverflow() ? m_overflow->layoutClientAfterEdge() : clientLogicalBottom();
954 computeOverflow(oldClientAfterEdge, true);
955
956 updateLayerTransform();
957
958 updateScrollInfoAfterLayout();
959
960 clearNeedsLayout();
961 return true;
962}
963
964void RenderBlock::markFixedPositionObjectForLayoutIfNeeded(RenderBox& positionedChild)
965{
966 if (positionedChild.style().position() != PositionType::Fixed)
967 return;
968
969 bool hasStaticBlockPosition = positionedChild.style().hasStaticBlockPosition(isHorizontalWritingMode());
970 bool hasStaticInlinePosition = positionedChild.style().hasStaticInlinePosition(isHorizontalWritingMode());
971 if (!hasStaticBlockPosition && !hasStaticInlinePosition)
972 return;
973
974 auto* parent = positionedChild.parent();
975 while (parent && !is<RenderView>(*parent) && parent->style().position() != PositionType::Absolute)
976 parent = parent->parent();
977 if (!parent || parent->style().position() != PositionType::Absolute)
978 return;
979
980 if (hasStaticInlinePosition) {
981 LogicalExtentComputedValues computedValues;
982 positionedChild.computeLogicalWidthInFragment(computedValues);
983 LayoutUnit newLeft = computedValues.m_position;
984 if (newLeft != positionedChild.logicalLeft())
985 positionedChild.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
986 } else if (hasStaticBlockPosition) {
987 LayoutUnit oldTop = positionedChild.logicalTop();
988 positionedChild.updateLogicalHeight();
989 if (positionedChild.logicalTop() != oldTop)
990 positionedChild.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
991 }
992}
993
994LayoutUnit RenderBlock::marginIntrinsicLogicalWidthForChild(RenderBox& child) const
995{
996 // A margin has three types: fixed, percentage, and auto (variable).
997 // Auto and percentage margins become 0 when computing min/max width.
998 // Fixed margins can be added in as is.
999 Length marginLeft = child.style().marginStartUsing(&style());
1000 Length marginRight = child.style().marginEndUsing(&style());
1001 LayoutUnit margin;
1002 if (marginLeft.isFixed())
1003 margin += marginLeft.value();
1004 if (marginRight.isFixed())
1005 margin += marginRight.value();
1006 return margin;
1007}
1008
1009void RenderBlock::layoutPositionedObject(RenderBox& r, bool relayoutChildren, bool fixedPositionObjectsOnly)
1010{
1011 estimateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(r);
1012
1013 // A fixed position element with an absolute positioned ancestor has no way of knowing if the latter has changed position. So
1014 // if this is a fixed position element, mark it for layout if it has an abspos ancestor and needs to move with that ancestor, i.e.
1015 // it has static position.
1016 markFixedPositionObjectForLayoutIfNeeded(r);
1017 if (fixedPositionObjectsOnly) {
1018 r.layoutIfNeeded();
1019 return;
1020 }
1021
1022 // When a non-positioned block element moves, it may have positioned children that are implicitly positioned relative to the
1023 // non-positioned block. Rather than trying to detect all of these movement cases, we just always lay out positioned
1024 // objects that are positioned implicitly like this. Such objects are rare, and so in typical DHTML menu usage (where everything is
1025 // positioned explicitly) this should not incur a performance penalty.
1026 if (relayoutChildren || (r.style().hasStaticBlockPosition(isHorizontalWritingMode()) && r.parent() != this))
1027 r.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1028
1029 // If relayoutChildren is set and the child has percentage padding or an embedded content box, we also need to invalidate the childs pref widths.
1030 if (relayoutChildren && r.needsPreferredWidthsRecalculation())
1031 r.setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(true, MarkOnlyThis);
1032
1033 r.markForPaginationRelayoutIfNeeded();
1034
1035 // We don't have to do a full layout. We just have to update our position. Try that first. If we have shrink-to-fit width
1036 // and we hit the available width constraint, the layoutIfNeeded() will catch it and do a full layout.
1037 if (r.needsPositionedMovementLayoutOnly() && r.tryLayoutDoingPositionedMovementOnly())
1038 r.clearNeedsLayout();
1039
1040 // If we are paginated or in a line grid, compute a vertical position for our object now.
1041 // If it's wrong we'll lay out again.
1042 LayoutUnit oldLogicalTop;
1043 bool needsBlockDirectionLocationSetBeforeLayout = r.needsLayout() && view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->needsBlockDirectionLocationSetBeforeLayout();
1044 if (needsBlockDirectionLocationSetBeforeLayout) {
1045 if (isHorizontalWritingMode() == r.isHorizontalWritingMode())
1046 r.updateLogicalHeight();
1047 else
1048 r.updateLogicalWidth();
1049 oldLogicalTop = logicalTopForChild(r);
1050 }
1051
1052 r.layoutIfNeeded();
1053
1054 auto* parent = r.parent();
1055 bool layoutChanged = false;
1056 if (parent->isFlexibleBox() && downcast<RenderFlexibleBox>(parent)->setStaticPositionForPositionedLayout(r)) {
1057 // The static position of an abspos child of a flexbox depends on its size
1058 // (for example, they can be centered). So we may have to reposition the
1059 // item after layout.
1060 // FIXME: We could probably avoid a layout here and just reposition?
1061 layoutChanged = true;
1062 }
1063
1064 // Lay out again if our estimate was wrong.
1065 if (layoutChanged || (needsBlockDirectionLocationSetBeforeLayout && logicalTopForChild(r) != oldLogicalTop)) {
1066 r.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1067 r.layoutIfNeeded();
1068 }
1069
1070 if (updateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(r)) {
1071 r.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1072 r.layoutIfNeeded();
1073 }
1074
1075 if (view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated() && is<RenderBlockFlow>(*this))
1076 downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*this).adjustSizeContainmentChildForPagination(r, r.logicalTop());
1077}
1078
1079void RenderBlock::layoutPositionedObjects(bool relayoutChildren, bool fixedPositionObjectsOnly)
1080{
1081 TrackedRendererListHashSet* positionedDescendants = positionedObjects();
1082 if (!positionedDescendants)
1083 return;
1084
1085 // Do not cache positionedDescendants->end() in a local variable, since |positionedDescendants| can be mutated
1086 // as it is walked. We always need to fetch the new end() value dynamically.
1087 for (auto it = positionedDescendants->begin(); it != positionedDescendants->end(); ++it)
1088 layoutPositionedObject(**it, relayoutChildren, fixedPositionObjectsOnly);
1089}
1090
1091void RenderBlock::markPositionedObjectsForLayout()
1092{
1093 TrackedRendererListHashSet* positionedDescendants = positionedObjects();
1094 if (!positionedDescendants)
1095 return;
1096
1097 for (auto it = positionedDescendants->begin(), end = positionedDescendants->end(); it != end; ++it) {
1098 RenderBox* r = *it;
1099 r->setChildNeedsLayout();
1100 }
1101}
1102
1103void RenderBlock::markForPaginationRelayoutIfNeeded()
1104{
1105 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
1106 if (needsLayout() || !layoutState->isPaginated())
1107 return;
1108
1109 if (layoutState->pageLogicalHeightChanged() || (layoutState->pageLogicalHeight() && layoutState->pageLogicalOffset(this, logicalTop()) != pageLogicalOffset()))
1110 setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1111}
1112
1113void RenderBlock::paint(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1114{
1115 LayoutPoint adjustedPaintOffset = paintOffset + location();
1116 PaintPhase phase = paintInfo.phase;
1117
1118 // Check if we need to do anything at all.
1119 // FIXME: Could eliminate the isDocumentElementRenderer() check if we fix background painting so that the RenderView
1120 // paints the root's background.
1121 if (!isDocumentElementRenderer() && !paintInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent)) {
1122 LayoutRect overflowBox = visualOverflowRect();
1123 flipForWritingMode(overflowBox);
1124 overflowBox.moveBy(adjustedPaintOffset);
1125 if (!overflowBox.intersects(paintInfo.rect))
1126 return;
1127 }
1128
1129 bool pushedClip = pushContentsClip(paintInfo, adjustedPaintOffset);
1130 paintObject(paintInfo, adjustedPaintOffset);
1131 if (pushedClip)
1132 popContentsClip(paintInfo, phase, adjustedPaintOffset);
1133
1134 // Our scrollbar widgets paint exactly when we tell them to, so that they work properly with
1135 // z-index. We paint after we painted the background/border, so that the scrollbars will
1136 // sit above the background/border.
1137 if ((phase == PaintPhase::BlockBackground || phase == PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackground) && hasOverflowClip() && layer()
1138 && layer()->scrollableArea() && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible && paintInfo.shouldPaintWithinRoot(*this) && !paintInfo.paintRootBackgroundOnly())
1139 layer()->scrollableArea()->paintOverflowControls(paintInfo.context(), roundedIntPoint(adjustedPaintOffset), snappedIntRect(paintInfo.rect));
1140}
1141
1142void RenderBlock::paintContents(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1143{
1144 // Style is non-final if the element has a pending stylesheet before it. We end up with renderers with such styles if a script
1145 // forces renderer construction by querying something layout dependent.
1146 // Avoid FOUC by not painting. Switching to final style triggers repaint.
1147 if (style().isNotFinal())
1148 return;
1149
1150 if (childrenInline())
1151 paintInlineChildren(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1152 else {
1153 PaintPhase newPhase = (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::ChildOutlines) ? PaintPhase::Outline : paintInfo.phase;
1154 newPhase = (newPhase == PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackgrounds) ? PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackground : newPhase;
1155
1156 // We don't paint our own background, but we do let the kids paint their backgrounds.
1157 PaintInfo paintInfoForChild(paintInfo);
1158 paintInfoForChild.phase = newPhase;
1159 paintInfoForChild.updateSubtreePaintRootForChildren(this);
1160
1161 if (paintInfo.eventRegionContext)
1162 paintInfoForChild.paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::EventRegionIncludeBackground);
1163
1164 // FIXME: Paint-time pagination is obsolete and is now only used by embedded WebViews inside AppKit
1165 // NSViews. Do not add any more code for this.
1166 bool usePrintRect = !view().printRect().isEmpty();
1167 paintChildren(paintInfo, paintOffset, paintInfoForChild, usePrintRect);
1168 }
1169}
1170
1171void RenderBlock::paintChildren(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, PaintInfo& paintInfoForChild, bool usePrintRect)
1172{
1173 for (auto* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
1174 if (!paintChild(*child, paintInfo, paintOffset, paintInfoForChild, usePrintRect))
1175 return;
1176 }
1177}
1178
1179bool RenderBlock::paintChild(RenderBox& child, PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, PaintInfo& paintInfoForChild, bool usePrintRect, PaintBlockType paintType)
1180{
1181 if (child.isExcludedAndPlacedInBorder())
1182 return true;
1183
1184 // Check for page-break-before: always, and if it's set, break and bail.
1185 bool checkBeforeAlways = !childrenInline() && (usePrintRect && alwaysPageBreak(child.style().breakBefore()));
1186 LayoutUnit absoluteChildY = paintOffset.y() + child.y();
1187 if (checkBeforeAlways
1188 && absoluteChildY > paintInfo.rect.y()
1189 && absoluteChildY < paintInfo.rect.maxY()) {
1190 view().setBestTruncatedAt(absoluteChildY, this, true);
1191 return false;
1192 }
1193
1194 if (!child.isFloating() && child.isReplaced() && usePrintRect && child.height() <= view().printRect().height()) {
1195 // Paginate block-level replaced elements.
1196 if (absoluteChildY + child.height() > view().printRect().maxY()) {
1197 if (absoluteChildY < view().truncatedAt())
1198 view().setBestTruncatedAt(absoluteChildY, &child);
1199 // If we were able to truncate, don't paint.
1200 if (absoluteChildY >= view().truncatedAt())
1201 return false;
1202 }
1203 }
1204
1205 LayoutPoint childPoint = flipForWritingModeForChild(&child, paintOffset);
1206 if (!child.hasSelfPaintingLayer() && !child.isFloating()) {
1207 if (paintType == PaintAsInlineBlock)
1208 child.paintAsInlineBlock(paintInfoForChild, childPoint);
1209 else
1210 child.paint(paintInfoForChild, childPoint);
1211 }
1212
1213 // Check for page-break-after: always, and if it's set, break and bail.
1214 bool checkAfterAlways = !childrenInline() && (usePrintRect && alwaysPageBreak(child.style().breakAfter()));
1215 if (checkAfterAlways
1216 && (absoluteChildY + child.height()) > paintInfo.rect.y()
1217 && (absoluteChildY + child.height()) < paintInfo.rect.maxY()) {
1218 view().setBestTruncatedAt(absoluteChildY + child.height() + std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, child.collapsedMarginAfter()), this, true);
1219 return false;
1220 }
1221
1222 return true;
1223}
1224
1225void RenderBlock::paintCaret(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, CaretType type)
1226{
1227 // Paint the caret if the FrameSelection says so or if caret browsing is enabled
1228 RenderBlock* caretPainter;
1229 bool isContentEditable;
1230 if (type == CursorCaret) {
1231 caretPainter = frame().selection().caretRendererWithoutUpdatingLayout();
1232 isContentEditable = frame().selection().selection().hasEditableStyle();
1233 } else {
1234 caretPainter = page().dragCaretController().caretRenderer();
1235 isContentEditable = page().dragCaretController().isContentEditable();
1236 }
1237
1238 if (caretPainter == this && (isContentEditable || settings().caretBrowsingEnabled())) {
1239 if (type == CursorCaret)
1240 frame().selection().paintCaret(paintInfo.context(), paintOffset, paintInfo.rect);
1241 else
1242 page().dragCaretController().paintDragCaret(&frame(), paintInfo.context(), paintOffset, paintInfo.rect);
1243 }
1244}
1245
1246void RenderBlock::paintObject(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1247{
1248 PaintPhase paintPhase = paintInfo.phase;
1249
1250 // 1. paint background, borders etc
1251 if ((paintPhase == PaintPhase::BlockBackground || paintPhase == PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackground) && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible) {
1252 if (hasVisibleBoxDecorations())
1253 paintBoxDecorations(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1254 }
1255
1256 // Paint legends just above the border before we scroll or clip.
1257 if (paintPhase == PaintPhase::BlockBackground || paintPhase == PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackground || paintPhase == PaintPhase::Selection)
1258 paintExcludedChildrenInBorder(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1259
1260 if (paintPhase == PaintPhase::Mask && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible) {
1261 paintMask(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1262 return;
1263 }
1264
1265 if (paintPhase == PaintPhase::ClippingMask && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible) {
1266 paintClippingMask(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1267 return;
1268 }
1269
1270 // If just painting the root background, then return.
1271 if (paintInfo.paintRootBackgroundOnly())
1272 return;
1273
1274 if (paintPhase == PaintPhase::EventRegion) {
1275 auto borderRect = LayoutRect(paintOffset, size());
1276
1277 if (paintInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::EventRegionIncludeBackground) && visibleToHitTesting()) {
1278 auto borderRegion = approximateAsRegion(style().getRoundedBorderFor(borderRect));
1279 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << "RenderBlock " << *this << " uniting region " << borderRegion);
1280 paintInfo.eventRegionContext->unite(borderRegion, style(), isTextControl() && downcast<RenderTextControl>(*this).textFormControlElement().isInnerTextElementEditable());
1281 }
1282
1283 if (!paintInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::EventRegionIncludeForeground))
1284 return;
1285
1286 bool needsTraverseDescendants = hasVisualOverflow() || containsFloats() || !paintInfo.eventRegionContext->contains(enclosingIntRect(borderRect)) || view().needsEventRegionUpdateForNonCompositedFrame();
1287 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << "RenderBlock " << *this << " needsTraverseDescendants for event region: hasVisualOverflow: " << hasVisualOverflow() << " containsFloats: "
1288 << containsFloats() << " border box is outside current region: " << !paintInfo.eventRegionContext->contains(enclosingIntRect(borderRect)) << " needsEventRegionUpdateForNonCompositedFrame:" << view().needsEventRegionUpdateForNonCompositedFrame());
1289#if ENABLE(TOUCH_ACTION_REGIONS)
1290 needsTraverseDescendants |= document().mayHaveElementsWithNonAutoTouchAction();
1291 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << " may have touch-action elements: " << document().mayHaveElementsWithNonAutoTouchAction());
1292#endif
1293#if ENABLE(WHEEL_EVENT_REGIONS)
1294 needsTraverseDescendants |= document().hasWheelEventHandlers();
1295 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << " has wheel event handlers: " << document().hasWheelEventHandlers());
1296#endif
1297#if ENABLE(EDITABLE_REGION)
1298 // We treat the entire text control as editable to match users' expectation even
1299 // though it's actually the inner text element of the control that is editable.
1300 // So, no need to traverse to find the inner text element in this case.
1301 if (!isTextControl()) {
1302 needsTraverseDescendants |= document().mayHaveEditableElements() && page().shouldBuildEditableRegion();
1303 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << " needs editable event region: " << (document().mayHaveEditableElements() && page().shouldBuildEditableRegion()));
1304 }
1305#endif
1306 if (!needsTraverseDescendants)
1307 return;
1308 }
1309
1310 // Adjust our painting position if we're inside a scrolled layer (e.g., an overflow:auto div).
1311 LayoutPoint scrolledOffset = paintOffset;
1312 scrolledOffset.moveBy(-scrollPosition());
1313
1314 // Column rules need to account for scrolling and clipping.
1315 // FIXME: Clipping of column rules does not work. We will need a separate paint phase for column rules I suspect in order to get
1316 // clipping correct (since it has to paint as background but is still considered "contents").
1317 if ((paintPhase == PaintPhase::BlockBackground || paintPhase == PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackground) && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible)
1318 paintColumnRules(paintInfo, scrolledOffset);
1319
1320 // Done with backgrounds, borders and column rules.
1321 if (paintPhase == PaintPhase::BlockBackground)
1322 return;
1323
1324 // 2. paint contents
1325 if (paintPhase != PaintPhase::SelfOutline)
1326 paintContents(paintInfo, scrolledOffset);
1327
1328 // 3. paint selection
1329 // FIXME: Make this work with multi column layouts. For now don't fill gaps.
1330 bool isPrinting = document().printing();
1331 if (!isPrinting)
1332 paintSelection(paintInfo, scrolledOffset); // Fill in gaps in selection on lines and between blocks.
1333
1334 // 4. paint floats.
1335 if (paintPhase == PaintPhase::Float || paintPhase == PaintPhase::Selection || paintPhase == PaintPhase::TextClip || paintPhase == PaintPhase::EventRegion)
1336 paintFloats(paintInfo, scrolledOffset, paintPhase == PaintPhase::Selection || paintPhase == PaintPhase::TextClip || paintPhase == PaintPhase::EventRegion);
1337
1338 // 5. paint outline.
1339 if ((paintPhase == PaintPhase::Outline || paintPhase == PaintPhase::SelfOutline) && hasOutline() && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible)
1340 paintOutline(paintInfo, LayoutRect(paintOffset, size()));
1341
1342 // 6. paint continuation outlines.
1343 if ((paintPhase == PaintPhase::Outline || paintPhase == PaintPhase::ChildOutlines)) {
1344 RenderInline* inlineCont = inlineContinuation();
1345 if (inlineCont && inlineCont->hasOutline() && inlineCont->style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible) {
1346 RenderInline* inlineRenderer = downcast<RenderInline>(inlineCont->element()->renderer());
1347 RenderBlock* containingBlock = this->containingBlock();
1348
1349 bool inlineEnclosedInSelfPaintingLayer = false;
1350 for (RenderBoxModelObject* box = inlineRenderer; box != containingBlock; box = &box->parent()->enclosingBoxModelObject()) {
1351 if (box->hasSelfPaintingLayer()) {
1352 inlineEnclosedInSelfPaintingLayer = true;
1353 break;
1354 }
1355 }
1356
1357 // Do not add continuations for outline painting by our containing block if we are a relative positioned
1358 // anonymous block (i.e. have our own layer), paint them straightaway instead. This is because a block depends on renderers in its continuation table being
1359 // in the same layer.
1360 if (!inlineEnclosedInSelfPaintingLayer && !hasLayer())
1361 containingBlock->addContinuationWithOutline(inlineRenderer);
1362 else if (!inlineRenderer->firstLineBox() || (!inlineEnclosedInSelfPaintingLayer && hasLayer()))
1363 inlineRenderer->paintOutline(paintInfo, paintOffset - locationOffset() + inlineRenderer->containingBlock()->location());
1364 }
1365 paintContinuationOutlines(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1366 }
1367
1368 // 7. paint caret.
1369 // If the caret's node's render object's containing block is this block, and the paint action is PaintPhase::Foreground,
1370 // then paint the caret.
1371 if (paintPhase == PaintPhase::Foreground) {
1372 paintCaret(paintInfo, paintOffset, CursorCaret);
1373 paintCaret(paintInfo, paintOffset, DragCaret);
1374 }
1375}
1376
1377static ContinuationOutlineTableMap* continuationOutlineTable()
1378{
1379 static NeverDestroyed<ContinuationOutlineTableMap> table;
1380 return &table.get();
1381}
1382
1383void RenderBlock::addContinuationWithOutline(RenderInline* flow)
1384{
1385 // We can't make this work if the inline is in a layer. We'll just rely on the broken
1386 // way of painting.
1387 ASSERT(!flow->layer() && !flow->isContinuation());
1388
1389 ContinuationOutlineTableMap* table = continuationOutlineTable();
1390 ListHashSet<RenderInline*>* continuations = table->get(this);
1391 if (!continuations) {
1392 continuations = new ListHashSet<RenderInline*>;
1393 table->set(this, std::unique_ptr<ListHashSet<RenderInline*>>(continuations));
1394 }
1395
1396 continuations->add(flow);
1397}
1398
1399bool RenderBlock::paintsContinuationOutline(RenderInline* flow)
1400{
1401 ContinuationOutlineTableMap* table = continuationOutlineTable();
1402 if (table->isEmpty())
1403 return false;
1404
1405 ListHashSet<RenderInline*>* continuations = table->get(this);
1406 if (!continuations)
1407 return false;
1408
1409 return continuations->contains(flow);
1410}
1411
1412void RenderBlock::paintContinuationOutlines(PaintInfo& info, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1413{
1414 ContinuationOutlineTableMap* table = continuationOutlineTable();
1415 if (table->isEmpty())
1416 return;
1417
1418 std::unique_ptr<ListHashSet<RenderInline*>> continuations = table->take(this);
1419 if (!continuations)
1420 return;
1421
1422 LayoutPoint accumulatedPaintOffset = paintOffset;
1423 // Paint each continuation outline.
1424 ListHashSet<RenderInline*>::iterator end = continuations->end();
1425 for (ListHashSet<RenderInline*>::iterator it = continuations->begin(); it != end; ++it) {
1426 // Need to add in the coordinates of the intervening blocks.
1427 RenderInline* flow = *it;
1428 RenderBlock* block = flow->containingBlock();
1429 for ( ; block && block != this; block = block->containingBlock())
1430 accumulatedPaintOffset.moveBy(block->location());
1431 ASSERT(block);
1432 flow->paintOutline(info, accumulatedPaintOffset);
1433 }
1434}
1435
1436bool RenderBlock::shouldPaintSelectionGaps() const
1437{
1438 if (settings().selectionPaintingWithoutSelectionGapsEnabled())
1439 return false;
1440
1441 return selectionState() != HighlightState::None && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible && isSelectionRoot();
1442}
1443
1444bool RenderBlock::isSelectionRoot() const
1445{
1446 if (isPseudoElement())
1447 return false;
1448 ASSERT(element() || isAnonymous());
1449
1450 // FIXME: Eventually tables should have to learn how to fill gaps between cells, at least in simple non-spanning cases.
1451 if (isTable())
1452 return false;
1453
1454 if (isBody() || isDocumentElementRenderer() || hasOverflowClip()
1455 || isPositioned() || isFloating()
1456 || isTableCell() || isInlineBlockOrInlineTable()
1457 || hasTransform() || hasReflection() || hasMask() || isWritingModeRoot()
1458 || isRenderFragmentedFlow() || style().columnSpan() == ColumnSpan::All)
1459 return true;
1460
1461 if (view().selection().start()) {
1462 Node* startElement = view().selection().start()->node();
1463 if (startElement && startElement->rootEditableElement() == element())
1464 return true;
1465 }
1466
1467 return false;
1468}
1469
1470GapRects RenderBlock::selectionGapRectsForRepaint(const RenderLayerModelObject* repaintContainer)
1471{
1472 ASSERT(!needsLayout());
1473
1474 if (!shouldPaintSelectionGaps())
1475 return GapRects();
1476
1477 FloatPoint containerPoint = localToContainerPoint(FloatPoint(), repaintContainer, UseTransforms);
1478 LayoutPoint offsetFromRepaintContainer(containerPoint - toFloatSize(scrollPosition()));
1479
1480 LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches cache(*this);
1481 LayoutUnit lastTop;
1482 LayoutUnit lastLeft = logicalLeftSelectionOffset(*this, lastTop, cache);
1483 LayoutUnit lastRight = logicalRightSelectionOffset(*this, lastTop, cache);
1484
1485 return selectionGaps(*this, offsetFromRepaintContainer, IntSize(), lastTop, lastLeft, lastRight, cache);
1486}
1487
1488void RenderBlock::paintSelection(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1489{
1490#if ENABLE(TEXT_SELECTION)
1491 if (shouldPaintSelectionGaps() && paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::Foreground) {
1492 LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches cache(*this);
1493 LayoutUnit lastTop;
1494 LayoutUnit lastLeft = logicalLeftSelectionOffset(*this, lastTop, cache);
1495 LayoutUnit lastRight = logicalRightSelectionOffset(*this, lastTop, cache);
1496 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(paintInfo.context());
1497
1498 LayoutRect gapRectsBounds = selectionGaps(*this, paintOffset, LayoutSize(), lastTop, lastLeft, lastRight, cache, &paintInfo);
1499 if (!gapRectsBounds.isEmpty()) {
1500 if (RenderLayer* layer = enclosingLayer()) {
1501 gapRectsBounds.moveBy(-paintOffset);
1502 if (!hasLayer()) {
1503 LayoutRect localBounds(gapRectsBounds);
1504 flipForWritingMode(localBounds);
1505 gapRectsBounds = localToContainerQuad(FloatRect(localBounds), &layer->renderer()).enclosingBoundingBox();
1506 if (layer->renderer().isBox())
1507 gapRectsBounds.moveBy(layer->renderBox()->scrollPosition());
1508 }
1509 layer->addBlockSelectionGapsBounds(gapRectsBounds);
1510 }
1511 }
1512 }
1513#else
1514 UNUSED_PARAM(paintInfo);
1515 UNUSED_PARAM(paintOffset);
1516#endif
1517}
1518
1519static void clipOutPositionedObjects(const PaintInfo* paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& offset, TrackedRendererListHashSet* positionedObjects)
1520{
1521 if (!positionedObjects)
1522 return;
1523
1524 TrackedRendererListHashSet::const_iterator end = positionedObjects->end();
1525 for (TrackedRendererListHashSet::const_iterator it = positionedObjects->begin(); it != end; ++it) {
1526 RenderBox* r = *it;
1527 paintInfo->context().clipOut(IntRect(offset.x() + r->x(), offset.y() + r->y(), r->width(), r->height()));
1528 }
1529}

1531LayoutUnit blockDirectionOffset(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock)
1532{
1533 return rootBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? offsetFromRootBlock.height() : offsetFromRootBlock.width();
1534}
1535
1536LayoutUnit inlineDirectionOffset(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock)
1537{
1538 return rootBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? offsetFromRootBlock.width() : offsetFromRootBlock.height();
1539}
1540
1541LayoutRect RenderBlock::logicalRectToPhysicalRect(const LayoutPoint& rootBlockPhysicalPosition, const LayoutRect& logicalRect)
1542{
1543 LayoutRect result;
1544 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
1545 result = logicalRect;
1546 else
1547 result = LayoutRect(logicalRect.y(), logicalRect.x(), logicalRect.height(), logicalRect.width());
1548 flipForWritingMode(result);
1549 result.moveBy(rootBlockPhysicalPosition);
1550 return result;
1551}
1552
1553GapRects RenderBlock::selectionGaps(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutPoint& rootBlockPhysicalPosition, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock,
1554 LayoutUnit& lastLogicalTop, LayoutUnit& lastLogicalLeft, LayoutUnit& lastLogicalRight, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache, const PaintInfo* paintInfo)
1555{
1556 // IMPORTANT: Callers of this method that intend for painting to happen need to do a save/restore.
1557 // Clip out floating and positioned objects when painting selection gaps.
1558 if (paintInfo) {
1559 // Note that we don't clip out overflow for positioned objects. We just stick to the border box.
1560 LayoutRect flippedBlockRect(offsetFromRootBlock.width(), offsetFromRootBlock.height(), width(), height());
1561 rootBlock.flipForWritingMode(flippedBlockRect);
1562 flippedBlockRect.moveBy(rootBlockPhysicalPosition);
1563 clipOutPositionedObjects(paintInfo, flippedBlockRect.location(), positionedObjects());
1564 if (isBody() || isDocumentElementRenderer()) { // The <body> must make sure to examine its containingBlock's positioned objects.
1565 for (RenderBlock* cb = containingBlock(); cb && !is<RenderView>(*cb); cb = cb->containingBlock())
1566 clipOutPositionedObjects(paintInfo, LayoutPoint(cb->x(), cb->y()), cb->positionedObjects()); // FIXME: Not right for flipped writing modes.
1567 }
1568 clipOutFloatingObjects(rootBlock, paintInfo, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock);
1569 }
1570
1571 // FIXME: overflow: auto/scroll fragments need more math here, since painting in the border box is different from painting in the padding box (one is scrolled, the other is
1572 // fixed).
1573 GapRects result;
1574 if (!isRenderBlockFlow()) // FIXME: Make multi-column selection gap filling work someday.
1575 return result;
1576
1577 if (hasTransform() || style().columnSpan() == ColumnSpan::All || isRenderFragmentedFlow()) {
1578 // FIXME: We should learn how to gap fill multiple columns and transforms eventually.
1579 lastLogicalTop = blockDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + logicalHeight();
1580 lastLogicalLeft = logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalHeight(), cache);
1581 lastLogicalRight = logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalHeight(), cache);
1582 return result;
1583 }
1584
1585 if (childrenInline())
1586 result = inlineSelectionGaps(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock, lastLogicalTop, lastLogicalLeft, lastLogicalRight, cache, paintInfo);
1587 else
1588 result = blockSelectionGaps(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock, lastLogicalTop, lastLogicalLeft, lastLogicalRight, cache, paintInfo);
1589
1590 // Fill the vertical gap all the way to the bottom of our block if the selection extends past our block.
1591 if (&rootBlock == this && (selectionState() != HighlightState::Both && selectionState() != HighlightState::End) && !isRubyBase() && !isRubyText()) {
1592 result.uniteCenter(blockSelectionGap(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock,
1593 lastLogicalTop, lastLogicalLeft, lastLogicalRight, logicalHeight(), cache, paintInfo));
1594 }
1595
1596 return result;
1597}
1598
1599GapRects RenderBlock::inlineSelectionGaps(RenderBlock&, const LayoutPoint&, const LayoutSize&, LayoutUnit&, LayoutUnit&, LayoutUnit&, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches&, const PaintInfo*)
1600{
1601 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1602 return GapRects();
1603}
1604
1605GapRects RenderBlock::blockSelectionGaps(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutPoint& rootBlockPhysicalPosition, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock,
1606 LayoutUnit& lastLogicalTop, LayoutUnit& lastLogicalLeft, LayoutUnit& lastLogicalRight, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache, const PaintInfo* paintInfo)
1607{
1608 GapRects result;
1609
1610 // Jump right to the first block child that contains some selected objects.
1611 RenderBox* curr;
1612 for (curr = firstChildBox(); curr && curr->selectionState() == HighlightState::None; curr = curr->nextSiblingBox()) { }
1613
1614 if (!curr)
1615 return result;
1616
1617 LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches childCache(*this, cache);
1618
1619 for (bool sawSelectionEnd = false; curr && !sawSelectionEnd; curr = curr->nextSiblingBox()) {
1620 HighlightState childState = curr->selectionState();
1621 if (childState == HighlightState::Both || childState == HighlightState::End)
1622 sawSelectionEnd = true;
1623
1624 if (curr->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
1625 continue; // We must be a normal flow object in order to even be considered.
1626
1627 if (curr->isInFlowPositioned() && curr->hasLayer()) {
1628 // If the relposition offset is anything other than 0, then treat this just like an absolute positioned element.
1629 // Just disregard it completely.
1630 LayoutSize relOffset = curr->layer()->offsetForInFlowPosition();
1631 if (relOffset.width() || relOffset.height())
1632 continue;
1633 }
1634
1635 bool paintsOwnSelection = curr->shouldPaintSelectionGaps() || curr->isTable(); // FIXME: Eventually we won't special-case table like this.
1636 bool fillBlockGaps = (paintsOwnSelection || (curr->canBeSelectionLeaf() && childState != HighlightState::None)) && !isRubyBase() && !isRubyText();
1637 if (fillBlockGaps) {
1638 // We need to fill the vertical gap above this object.
1639 if (childState == HighlightState::End || childState == HighlightState::Inside) {
1640 // Fill the gap above the object.
1641 result.uniteCenter(blockSelectionGap(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock,
1642 lastLogicalTop, lastLogicalLeft, lastLogicalRight, curr->logicalTop(), cache, paintInfo));
1643 }
1644
1645 // Only fill side gaps for objects that paint their own selection if we know for sure the selection is going to extend all the way *past*
1646 // our object. We know this if the selection did not end inside our object.
1647 if (paintsOwnSelection && (childState == HighlightState::Start || sawSelectionEnd))
1648 childState = HighlightState::None;
1649
1650 // Fill side gaps on this object based off its state.
1651 bool leftGap, rightGap;
1652 getSelectionGapInfo(childState, leftGap, rightGap);
1653
1654 if (leftGap)
1655 result.uniteLeft(logicalLeftSelectionGap(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock, this, curr->logicalLeft(), curr->logicalTop(), curr->logicalHeight(), cache, paintInfo));
1656 if (rightGap)
1657 result.uniteRight(logicalRightSelectionGap(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock, this, curr->logicalRight(), curr->logicalTop(), curr->logicalHeight(), cache, paintInfo));
1658
1659 // Update lastLogicalTop to be just underneath the object. lastLogicalLeft and lastLogicalRight extend as far as
1660 // they can without bumping into floating or positioned objects. Ideally they will go right up
1661 // to the border of the root selection block.
1662 lastLogicalTop = blockDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + curr->logicalBottom();
1663 lastLogicalLeft = logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, curr->logicalBottom(), cache);
1664 lastLogicalRight = logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, curr->logicalBottom(), cache);
1665 } else if (childState != HighlightState::None && is<RenderBlock>(*curr)) {
1666 // We must be a block that has some selected object inside it, so recur.
1667 result.unite(downcast<RenderBlock>(*curr).selectionGaps(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, LayoutSize(offsetFromRootBlock.width() + curr->x(), offsetFromRootBlock.height() + curr->y()),
1668 lastLogicalTop, lastLogicalLeft, lastLogicalRight, childCache, paintInfo));
1669 }
1670 }
1671 return result;
1672}
1673
1674LayoutRect RenderBlock::blockSelectionGap(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutPoint& rootBlockPhysicalPosition, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock,
1675 LayoutUnit lastLogicalTop, LayoutUnit lastLogicalLeft, LayoutUnit lastLogicalRight, LayoutUnit logicalBottom, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache, const PaintInfo* paintInfo)
1676{
1677 LayoutUnit logicalTop = lastLogicalTop;
1678 LayoutUnit logicalHeight = blockDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + logicalBottom - logicalTop;
1679 if (logicalHeight <= 0)
1680 return LayoutRect();
1681
1682 // Get the selection offsets for the bottom of the gap
1683 LayoutUnit logicalLeft = std::max(lastLogicalLeft, logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalBottom, cache));
1684 LayoutUnit logicalRight = std::min(lastLogicalRight, logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalBottom, cache));
1685 LayoutUnit logicalWidth = logicalRight - logicalLeft;
1686 if (logicalWidth <= 0)
1687 return LayoutRect();
1688
1689 LayoutRect gapRect = rootBlock.logicalRectToPhysicalRect(rootBlockPhysicalPosition, LayoutRect(logicalLeft, logicalTop, logicalWidth, logicalHeight));
1690 if (paintInfo)
1691 paintInfo->context().fillRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(gapRect, document().deviceScaleFactor()), selectionBackgroundColor());
1692 return gapRect;
1693}
1694
1695LayoutRect RenderBlock::logicalLeftSelectionGap(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutPoint& rootBlockPhysicalPosition, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock,
1696 RenderBoxModelObject* selObj, LayoutUnit logicalLeft, LayoutUnit logicalTop, LayoutUnit logicalHeight, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache, const PaintInfo* paintInfo)
1697{
1698 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalTop = blockDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + logicalTop;
1699 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalLeft = std::max(logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop, cache), logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop + logicalHeight, cache));
1700 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalRight = std::min(inlineDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + logicalLeft,
1701 std::min(logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop, cache), logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop + logicalHeight, cache)));
1702 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalWidth = rootBlockLogicalRight - rootBlockLogicalLeft;
1703 if (rootBlockLogicalWidth <= 0)
1704 return LayoutRect();
1705
1706 LayoutRect gapRect = rootBlock.logicalRectToPhysicalRect(rootBlockPhysicalPosition, LayoutRect(rootBlockLogicalLeft, rootBlockLogicalTop, rootBlockLogicalWidth, logicalHeight));
1707 if (paintInfo)
1708 paintInfo->context().fillRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(gapRect, document().deviceScaleFactor()), selObj->selectionBackgroundColor());
1709 return gapRect;
1710}
1711
1712LayoutRect RenderBlock::logicalRightSelectionGap(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutPoint& rootBlockPhysicalPosition, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock,
1713 RenderBoxModelObject* selObj, LayoutUnit logicalRight, LayoutUnit logicalTop, LayoutUnit logicalHeight, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache, const PaintInfo* paintInfo)
1714{
1715 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalTop = blockDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + logicalTop;
1716 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalLeft = std::max(inlineDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + logicalRight,
1717 std::max(logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop, cache), logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop + logicalHeight, cache)));
1718 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalRight = std::min(logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop, cache), logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalTop + logicalHeight, cache));
1719 LayoutUnit rootBlockLogicalWidth = rootBlockLogicalRight - rootBlockLogicalLeft;
1720 if (rootBlockLogicalWidth <= 0)
1721 return LayoutRect();
1722
1723 LayoutRect gapRect = rootBlock.logicalRectToPhysicalRect(rootBlockPhysicalPosition, LayoutRect(rootBlockLogicalLeft, rootBlockLogicalTop, rootBlockLogicalWidth, logicalHeight));
1724 if (paintInfo)
1725 paintInfo->context().fillRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(gapRect, document().deviceScaleFactor()), selObj->selectionBackgroundColor());
1726 return gapRect;
1727}
1728
1729void RenderBlock::getSelectionGapInfo(HighlightState state, bool& leftGap, bool& rightGap)
1730{
1731 bool ltr = style().isLeftToRightDirection();
1732 leftGap = (state == RenderObject::HighlightState::Inside) || (state == RenderObject::HighlightState::End && ltr) || (state == RenderObject::HighlightState::Start && !ltr);
1733 rightGap = (state == RenderObject::HighlightState::Inside) || (state == RenderObject::HighlightState::Start && ltr) || (state == RenderObject::HighlightState::End && !ltr);
1734}
1735
1736LayoutUnit RenderBlock::logicalLeftSelectionOffset(RenderBlock& rootBlock, LayoutUnit position, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache)
1737{
1738 LayoutUnit logicalLeft = logicalLeftOffsetForLine(position, DoNotIndentText);
1739 if (logicalLeft == logicalLeftOffsetForContent()) {
1740 if (&rootBlock != this) // The border can potentially be further extended by our containingBlock().
1741 return cache.containingBlockInfo(*this).logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, position + logicalTop());
1742 return logicalLeft;
1743 }
1744
1745 RenderBlock* cb = this;
1746 const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches* currentCache = &cache;
1747 while (cb != &rootBlock) {
1748 logicalLeft += cb->logicalLeft();
1749
1750 ASSERT(currentCache);
1751 auto info = currentCache->containingBlockInfo(*cb);
1752 cb = info.block();
1753 if (!cb)
1754 break;
1755 currentCache = info.cache();
1756 }
1757 return logicalLeft;
1758}
1759
1760LayoutUnit RenderBlock::logicalRightSelectionOffset(RenderBlock& rootBlock, LayoutUnit position, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache)
1761{
1762 LayoutUnit logicalRight = logicalRightOffsetForLine(position, DoNotIndentText);
1763 if (logicalRight == logicalRightOffsetForContent()) {
1764 if (&rootBlock != this) // The border can potentially be further extended by our containingBlock().
1765 return cache.containingBlockInfo(*this).logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, position + logicalTop());
1766 return logicalRight;
1767 }
1768
1769 RenderBlock* cb = this;
1770 const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches* currentCache = &cache;
1771 while (cb != &rootBlock) {
1772 logicalRight += cb->logicalLeft();
1773
1774 ASSERT(currentCache);
1775 auto info = currentCache->containingBlockInfo(*cb);
1776 cb = info.block();
1777 if (!cb)
1778 break;
1779 currentCache = info.cache();
1780 }
1781 return logicalRight;
1782}

1789void RenderBlock::insertPositionedObject(RenderBox& positioned)
1790{
1791 ASSERT(!isAnonymousBlock());
1792
1793 positioned.clearOverridingContainingBlockContentSize();
1794
1795 if (positioned.isRenderFragmentedFlow())
1796 return;
1797 // FIXME: Find out if we can do this as part of positioned.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis)
1798 if (positioned.needsLayout()) {
1799 // We should turn this bit on only while in layout.
1800 ASSERT(posChildNeedsLayout() || view().frameView().layoutContext().isInLayout());
1801 setPosChildNeedsLayoutBit(true);
1802 }
1803 positionedDescendantsMap().addDescendant(*this, positioned, isRenderView() ? PositionedDescendantsMap::MoveDescendantToEnd::Yes
1804 : PositionedDescendantsMap::MoveDescendantToEnd::No);
1805}

1808{
1809 positionedDescendantsMap().removeDescendant(rendererToRemove);
1810}
1811
1812void RenderBlock::removePositionedObjects(const RenderBlock* newContainingBlockCandidate, ContainingBlockState containingBlockState)
1813{
1814 auto* positionedDescendants = positionedObjects();
1815 if (!positionedDescendants)
1816 return;
1817
1818 Vector<RenderBox*, 16> renderersToRemove;
1819 for (auto* renderer : *positionedDescendants) {
1820 if (newContainingBlockCandidate && !renderer->isDescendantOf(newContainingBlockCandidate))
1821 continue;
1822 renderersToRemove.append(renderer);
1823 if (containingBlockState == NewContainingBlock)
1824 renderer->setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1825 // It is the parent block's job to add positioned children to positioned objects list of its containing block.
1826 // Dirty the parent to ensure this happens. We also need to make sure the new containing block is dirty as well so
1827 // that it gets to these new positioned objects.
1828 auto* parent = renderer->parent();
1829 while (parent && !is<RenderBlock>(parent))
1830 parent = parent->parent();
1831 if (parent)
1832 parent->setChildNeedsLayout();
1833
1834 if (renderer->isFixedPositioned())
1835 view().setNeedsLayout();
1836 else if (auto* newContainingBlock = containingBlock()) {
1837 // During style change, at this point the renderer's containing block is still "this" renderer, and "this" renderer is still positioned.
1838 // FIXME: During subtree moving, this is mostly invalid but either the subtree is detached (we don't even get here) or renderers
1839 // are already marked dirty.
1840 for (; newContainingBlock && !newContainingBlock->canContainAbsolutelyPositionedObjects(); newContainingBlock = newContainingBlock->containingBlock()) { }
1841 if (newContainingBlock)
1842 newContainingBlock->setNeedsLayout();
1843 }
1844 }
1845 for (auto* renderer : renderersToRemove)
1846 removePositionedObject(*renderer);
1847}
