1946
1947LayoutUnit RenderBlock::adjustLogicalLeftOffsetForLine(LayoutUnit offsetFromFloats, bool applyTextIndent) const
1948{
1949 LayoutUnit left = offsetFromFloats;
1950
1951 if (applyTextIndent && style().isLeftToRightDirection())
1952 left += textIndentOffset();
1953
1954 if (style().lineAlign() == LineAlign::None)
1955 return left;
1956
1957 // Push in our left offset so that it is aligned with the character grid.
1958 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
1959 if (!layoutState)
1960 return left;
1961
1962 RenderBlock* lineGrid = layoutState->lineGrid();
1963 if (!lineGrid || lineGrid->style().writingMode() != style().writingMode())
1964 return left;
1965
1966 // FIXME: Should letter-spacing apply? This is complicated since it doesn't apply at the edge?
1967 float maxCharWidth = lineGrid->style().fontCascade().primaryFont().maxCharWidth();
1968 if (!maxCharWidth)
1969 return left;
1970
1971 LayoutUnit lineGridOffset = lineGrid->isHorizontalWritingMode() ? layoutState->lineGridOffset().width(): layoutState->lineGridOffset().height();
1972 LayoutUnit layoutOffset = lineGrid->isHorizontalWritingMode() ? layoutState->layoutOffset().width() : layoutState->layoutOffset().height();
1973
1974 // Push in to the nearest character width (truncated so that we pixel snap left).
1975 // FIXME: Should be patched when subpixel layout lands, since this calculation doesn't have to pixel snap
1976 // any more (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79946).
1977 // FIXME: This is wrong for RTL (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79945).
1978 // FIXME: This doesn't work with columns or fragments (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79942).
1979 // FIXME: This doesn't work when the inline position of the object isn't set ahead of time.
1980 // FIXME: Dynamic changes to the font or to the inline position need to result in a deep relayout.
1981 // (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79944)
1982 float remainder = fmodf(maxCharWidth - fmodf(left + layoutOffset - lineGridOffset, maxCharWidth), maxCharWidth);
1983 left += remainder;
1984 return left;
1985}
1986
1987LayoutUnit RenderBlock::adjustLogicalRightOffsetForLine(LayoutUnit offsetFromFloats, bool applyTextIndent) const
1988{
1989 LayoutUnit right = offsetFromFloats;
1990
1991 if (applyTextIndent && !style().isLeftToRightDirection())
1992 right -= textIndentOffset();
1993
1994 if (style().lineAlign() == LineAlign::None)
1995 return right;
1996
1997 // Push in our right offset so that it is aligned with the character grid.
1998 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
1999 if (!layoutState)
2000 return right;
2001
2002 RenderBlock* lineGrid = layoutState->lineGrid();
2003 if (!lineGrid || lineGrid->style().writingMode() != style().writingMode())
2004 return right;
2005
2006 // FIXME: Should letter-spacing apply? This is complicated since it doesn't apply at the edge?
2007 float maxCharWidth = lineGrid->style().fontCascade().primaryFont().maxCharWidth();
2008 if (!maxCharWidth)
2009 return right;
2010
2011 LayoutUnit lineGridOffset = lineGrid->isHorizontalWritingMode() ? layoutState->lineGridOffset().width(): layoutState->lineGridOffset().height();
2012 LayoutUnit layoutOffset = lineGrid->isHorizontalWritingMode() ? layoutState->layoutOffset().width() : layoutState->layoutOffset().height();
2013
2014 // Push in to the nearest character width (truncated so that we pixel snap right).
2015 // FIXME: Should be patched when subpixel layout lands, since this calculation doesn't have to pixel snap
2016 // any more (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79946).
2017 // FIXME: This is wrong for RTL (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79945).
2018 // FIXME: This doesn't work with columns or fragments (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79942).
2019 // FIXME: This doesn't work when the inline position of the object isn't set ahead of time.
2020 // FIXME: Dynamic changes to the font or to the inline position need to result in a deep relayout.
2021 // (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=79944)
2022 float remainder = fmodf(fmodf(right + layoutOffset - lineGridOffset, maxCharWidth), maxCharWidth);
2023 right -= ceilf(remainder);
2024 return right;
2025}

2028{
2029 if (!scrollsOverflow())
2030 return false;

2044bool RenderBlock::hitTestChildren(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const HitTestLocation& locationInContainer, const LayoutPoint& adjustedLocation, HitTestAction hitTestAction)
2045{
2046 // Hit test descendants first.
2047 const LayoutSize localOffset = toLayoutSize(adjustedLocation);
2048 const LayoutSize scrolledOffset(localOffset - toLayoutSize(scrollPosition()));
2049
2050 if (hitTestAction == HitTestFloat && hitTestFloats(request, result, locationInContainer, toLayoutPoint(scrolledOffset)))
2051 return true;
2052 if (hitTestContents(request, result, locationInContainer, toLayoutPoint(scrolledOffset), hitTestAction)) {
2053 updateHitTestResult(result, flipForWritingMode(locationInContainer.point() - localOffset));
2054 return true;
2055 }
2056 return false;
2057}
2058
2059bool RenderBlock::nodeAtPoint(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const HitTestLocation& locationInContainer, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset, HitTestAction hitTestAction)
2060{
2061 const LayoutPoint adjustedLocation(accumulatedOffset + location());
2062 const LayoutSize localOffset = toLayoutSize(adjustedLocation);
2063
2064 // Check if we need to do anything at all.
2065 if (!hitTestVisualOverflow(locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
2066 return false;
2067
2068 if ((hitTestAction == HitTestBlockBackground || hitTestAction == HitTestChildBlockBackground) && isPointInOverflowControl(result, locationInContainer.point(), adjustedLocation)) {
2069 updateHitTestResult(result, locationInContainer.point() - localOffset);
2070 // FIXME: isPointInOverflowControl() doesn't handle rect-based tests yet.
2071 if (result.addNodeToListBasedTestResult(nodeForHitTest(), request, locationInContainer) == HitTestProgress::Stop)
2072 return true;
2073 }
2074
2075 if (!hitTestClipPath(locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
2076 return false;
2077
2078 // If we have clipping, then we can't have any spillout.
2079 bool useClip = (hasControlClip() || hasOverflowClip());
2080 bool checkChildren = !useClip || (hasControlClip() ? locationInContainer.intersects(controlClipRect(adjustedLocation)) : locationInContainer.intersects(overflowClipRect(adjustedLocation, nullptr, IncludeOverlayScrollbarSize)));
2081 if (checkChildren && hitTestChildren(request, result, locationInContainer, adjustedLocation, hitTestAction))
2082 return true;
2083
2084 if (!checkChildren && hitTestExcludedChildrenInBorder(request, result, locationInContainer, adjustedLocation, hitTestAction))
2085 return true;
2086
2087 if (!hitTestBorderRadius(locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
2088 return false;
2089
2090 // Now hit test our background
2091 if (hitTestAction == HitTestBlockBackground || hitTestAction == HitTestChildBlockBackground) {
2092 LayoutRect boundsRect(adjustedLocation, size());
2093 if (visibleToHitTesting(request) && locationInContainer.intersects(boundsRect)) {
2094 updateHitTestResult(result, flipForWritingMode(locationInContainer.point() - localOffset));
2095 if (result.addNodeToListBasedTestResult(nodeForHitTest(), request, locationInContainer, boundsRect) == HitTestProgress::Stop)
2096 return true;
2097 }
2098 }
2099
2100 return false;
2101}
2102
2103bool RenderBlock::hitTestContents(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const HitTestLocation& locationInContainer, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset, HitTestAction hitTestAction)
2104{
2105 if (childrenInline() && !isTable())
2106 return hitTestInlineChildren(request, result, locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset, hitTestAction);
2107
2108 // Hit test our children.
2109 HitTestAction childHitTest = hitTestAction;
2110 if (hitTestAction == HitTestChildBlockBackgrounds)
2111 childHitTest = HitTestChildBlockBackground;
2112 for (auto* child = lastChildBox(); child; child = child->previousSiblingBox()) {
2113 LayoutPoint childPoint = flipForWritingModeForChild(child, accumulatedOffset);
2114 if (!child->hasSelfPaintingLayer() && !child->isFloating() && child->nodeAtPoint(request, result, locationInContainer, childPoint, childHitTest))
2115 return true;
2116 }
2117
2118 return false;
2119}

2121static inline bool isEditingBoundary(RenderElement* ancestor, RenderObject& child)
2122{
2123 ASSERT(!ancestor || ancestor->nonPseudoElement());
2124 ASSERT(child.nonPseudoNode());
2125 return !ancestor || !ancestor->parent() || (ancestor->hasLayer() && ancestor->parent()->isRenderView())
2126 || ancestor->nonPseudoElement()->hasEditableStyle() == child.nonPseudoNode()->hasEditableStyle();
2127}
2128
2129// FIXME: This function should go on RenderObject as an instance method. Then
2130// all cases in which positionForPoint recurs could call this instead to
2131// prevent crossing editable boundaries. This would require many tests.
2132VisiblePosition positionForPointRespectingEditingBoundaries(RenderBlock& parent, RenderBox& child, const LayoutPoint& pointInParentCoordinates)
2133{
2134 LayoutPoint childLocation = child.location();
2135 if (child.isInFlowPositioned())
2136 childLocation += child.offsetForInFlowPosition();
2137
2138 // FIXME: This is wrong if the child's writing-mode is different from the parent's.
2139 LayoutPoint pointInChildCoordinates(toLayoutPoint(pointInParentCoordinates - childLocation));
2140
2141 // If this is an anonymous renderer, we just recur normally
2142 Element* childElement= child.nonPseudoElement();
2143 if (!childElement)
2144 return child.positionForPoint(pointInChildCoordinates, nullptr);
2145
2146 // Otherwise, first make sure that the editability of the parent and child agree.
2147 // If they don't agree, then we return a visible position just before or after the child
2148 RenderElement* ancestor = &parent;
2149 while (ancestor && !ancestor->nonPseudoElement())
2150 ancestor = ancestor->parent();
2151
2152 // If we can't find an ancestor to check editability on, or editability is unchanged, we recur like normal
2153 if (isEditingBoundary(ancestor, child))
2154 return child.positionForPoint(pointInChildCoordinates, nullptr);
2155
2156 // Otherwise return before or after the child, depending on if the click was to the logical left or logical right of the child
2157 LayoutUnit childMiddle = parent.logicalWidthForChild(child) / 2;
2158 LayoutUnit logicalLeft = parent.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? pointInChildCoordinates.x() : pointInChildCoordinates.y();
2159 if (logicalLeft < childMiddle)
2160 return ancestor->createVisiblePosition(childElement->computeNodeIndex(), Affinity::Downstream);
2161 return ancestor->createVisiblePosition(childElement->computeNodeIndex() + 1, Affinity::Upstream);
2162}

2165{
2166 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2167 return VisiblePosition();

2170static inline bool isChildHitTestCandidate(const RenderBox& box)
2171{
2172 return box.height() && box.style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible && !box.isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !box.isRenderFragmentedFlow();
2173}
2174
2175// Valid candidates in a FragmentedFlow must be rendered by the fragment.
2176static inline bool isChildHitTestCandidate(const RenderBox& box, const RenderFragmentContainer* fragment, const LayoutPoint& point)
2177{
2178 if (!isChildHitTestCandidate(box))
2179 return false;
2180 if (!fragment)
2181 return true;
2182 const RenderBlock& block = is<RenderBlock>(box) ? downcast<RenderBlock>(box) : *box.containingBlock();
2183 return block.fragmentAtBlockOffset(point.y()) == fragment;
2184}
2185
2186VisiblePosition RenderBlock::positionForPoint(const LayoutPoint& point, const RenderFragmentContainer* fragment)
2187{
2188 if (isTable())
2189 return RenderBox::positionForPoint(point, fragment);
2190
2191 if (isReplaced()) {
2192 // FIXME: This seems wrong when the object's writing-mode doesn't match the line's writing-mode.
2193 LayoutUnit pointLogicalLeft = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? point.x() : point.y();
2194 LayoutUnit pointLogicalTop = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? point.y() : point.x();
2195
2196 if (pointLogicalTop < 0 || (pointLogicalTop < logicalHeight() && pointLogicalLeft < 0))
2197 return createVisiblePosition(caretMinOffset(), Affinity::Downstream);
2198 if (pointLogicalTop >= logicalHeight() || (pointLogicalTop >= 0 && pointLogicalLeft >= logicalWidth()))
2199 return createVisiblePosition(caretMaxOffset(), Affinity::Downstream);
2200 }
2201 if (isFlexibleBoxIncludingDeprecated() || isRenderGrid())
2202 return RenderBox::positionForPoint(point, fragment);
2203
2204 LayoutPoint pointInContents = point;
2205 offsetForContents(pointInContents);
2206 LayoutPoint pointInLogicalContents(pointInContents);
2207 if (!isHorizontalWritingMode())
2208 pointInLogicalContents = pointInLogicalContents.transposedPoint();
2209
2210 if (childrenInline())
2211 return positionForPointWithInlineChildren(pointInLogicalContents, fragment);
2212
2213 RenderBox* lastCandidateBox = lastChildBox();
2214
2215 if (!fragment)
2216 fragment = fragmentAtBlockOffset(pointInLogicalContents.y());
2217
2218 while (lastCandidateBox && !isChildHitTestCandidate(*lastCandidateBox, fragment, pointInLogicalContents))
2219 lastCandidateBox = lastCandidateBox->previousSiblingBox();
2220
2221 bool blocksAreFlipped = style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode();
2222 if (lastCandidateBox) {
2223 if (pointInLogicalContents.y() > logicalTopForChild(*lastCandidateBox)
2224 || (!blocksAreFlipped && pointInLogicalContents.y() == logicalTopForChild(*lastCandidateBox)))
2225 return positionForPointRespectingEditingBoundaries(*this, *lastCandidateBox, pointInContents);
2226
2227 for (auto* childBox = firstChildBox(); childBox; childBox = childBox->nextSiblingBox()) {
2228 if (!isChildHitTestCandidate(*childBox, fragment, pointInLogicalContents))
2229 continue;
2230 auto childLogicalBottom = logicalTopForChild(*childBox) + logicalHeightForChild(*childBox);
2231 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(childBox))
2232 childLogicalBottom = std::max(childLogicalBottom, downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*childBox).lowestFloatLogicalBottom());
2233 // We hit child if our click is above the bottom of its padding box (like IE6/7 and FF3).
2234 if (pointInLogicalContents.y() < childLogicalBottom || (blocksAreFlipped && pointInLogicalContents.y() == childLogicalBottom))
2235 return positionForPointRespectingEditingBoundaries(*this, *childBox, pointInContents);
2236 }
2237 }
2238
2239 // We only get here if there are no hit test candidate children below the click.
2240 return RenderBox::positionForPoint(point, fragment);
2241}

2244{
2245 offset = flipForWritingMode(offset);
2246 offset += toLayoutSize(scrollPosition());
2247 offset = flipForWritingMode(offset);
2248}

2251{
2252 ASSERT(!childrenInline());
2253 if (!shouldApplySizeContainment(*this))
2254 computeBlockPreferredLogicalWidths(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2255
2256 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2257

2262
2263void RenderBlock::computePreferredLogicalWidths()
2264{
2265 ASSERT(preferredLogicalWidthsDirty());
2266
2267 m_minPreferredLogicalWidth = 0;
2268 m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth = 0;
2269
2270 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
2271 if (!isTableCell() && styleToUse.logicalWidth().isFixed() && styleToUse.logicalWidth().value() >= 0
2272 && !(isDeprecatedFlexItem() && !styleToUse.logicalWidth().intValue()))
2273 m_minPreferredLogicalWidth = m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth = adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(styleToUse.logicalWidth());
2274 else if (shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio())
2275 m_minPreferredLogicalWidth = m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth = computeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio();
2276 else
2277 computeIntrinsicLogicalWidths(m_minPreferredLogicalWidth, m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth);
2278
2279 RenderBox::computePreferredLogicalWidths(styleToUse.logicalMinWidth(), styleToUse.logicalMaxWidth(), borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth());
2280
2281 setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(false);
2282}
2283
2284void RenderBlock::computeBlockPreferredLogicalWidths(LayoutUnit& minLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxLogicalWidth) const
2285{
2286 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
2287 bool nowrap = styleToUse.whiteSpace() == WhiteSpace::NoWrap;
2288
2289 RenderObject* child = firstChild();
2290 RenderBlock* containingBlock = this->containingBlock();
2291 LayoutUnit floatLeftWidth, floatRightWidth;
2292
2293 LayoutUnit childMinWidth;
2294 LayoutUnit childMaxWidth;
2295 bool hadExcludedChildren = computePreferredWidthsForExcludedChildren(childMinWidth, childMaxWidth);
2296 if (hadExcludedChildren) {
2297 minLogicalWidth = std::max(childMinWidth, minLogicalWidth);
2298 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(childMaxWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2299 }
2300
2301 while (child) {
2302 // Positioned children don't affect the min/max width. Legends in fieldsets are skipped here
2303 // since they compute outside of any one layout system. Other children excluded from
2304 // normal layout are only used with block flows, so it's ok to calculate them here.
2305 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned() || child->isExcludedAndPlacedInBorder()) {
2306 child = child->nextSibling();
2307 continue;
2308 }
2309
2310 const RenderStyle& childStyle = child->style();
2311 if (child->isFloating() || (is<RenderBox>(*child) && downcast<RenderBox>(*child).avoidsFloats())) {
2312 LayoutUnit floatTotalWidth = floatLeftWidth + floatRightWidth;
2313 auto childUsedClear = RenderStyle::usedClear(*child);
2314 if (childUsedClear == UsedClear::Left || childUsedClear == UsedClear::Both) {
2315 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(floatTotalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2316 floatLeftWidth = 0;
2317 }
2318 if (childUsedClear == UsedClear::Right || childUsedClear == UsedClear::Both) {
2319 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(floatTotalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2320 floatRightWidth = 0;
2321 }
2322 }
2323
2324 // A margin basically has three types: fixed, percentage, and auto (variable).
2325 // Auto and percentage margins simply become 0 when computing min/max width.
2326 // Fixed margins can be added in as is.
2327 Length startMarginLength = childStyle.marginStartUsing(&styleToUse);
2328 Length endMarginLength = childStyle.marginEndUsing(&styleToUse);
2329 LayoutUnit margin;
2330 LayoutUnit marginStart;
2331 LayoutUnit marginEnd;
2332 if (startMarginLength.isFixed())
2333 marginStart += startMarginLength.value();
2334 if (endMarginLength.isFixed())
2335 marginEnd += endMarginLength.value();
2336 margin = marginStart + marginEnd;
2337
2338 LayoutUnit childMinPreferredLogicalWidth, childMaxPreferredLogicalWidth;
2339 computeChildPreferredLogicalWidths(*child, childMinPreferredLogicalWidth, childMaxPreferredLogicalWidth);
2340
2341 LayoutUnit w = childMinPreferredLogicalWidth + margin;
2342 minLogicalWidth = std::max(w, minLogicalWidth);
2343
2344 // IE ignores tables for calculation of nowrap. Makes some sense.
2345 if (nowrap && !child->isTable())
2346 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(w, maxLogicalWidth);
2347
2348 w = childMaxPreferredLogicalWidth + margin;
2349
2350 if (!child->isFloating()) {
2351 if (is<RenderBox>(*child) && downcast<RenderBox>(*child).avoidsFloats()) {
2352 // Determine a left and right max value based off whether or not the floats can fit in the
2353 // margins of the object. For negative margins, we will attempt to overlap the float if the negative margin
2354 // is smaller than the float width.
2355 bool ltr = containingBlock ? containingBlock->style().isLeftToRightDirection() : styleToUse.isLeftToRightDirection();
2356 LayoutUnit marginLogicalLeft = ltr ? marginStart : marginEnd;
2357 LayoutUnit marginLogicalRight = ltr ? marginEnd : marginStart;
2358 LayoutUnit maxLeft = marginLogicalLeft > 0 ? std::max(floatLeftWidth, marginLogicalLeft) : floatLeftWidth + marginLogicalLeft;
2359 LayoutUnit maxRight = marginLogicalRight > 0 ? std::max(floatRightWidth, marginLogicalRight) : floatRightWidth + marginLogicalRight;
2360 w = childMaxPreferredLogicalWidth + maxLeft + maxRight;
2361 w = std::max(w, floatLeftWidth + floatRightWidth);
2362 }
2363 else
2364 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(floatLeftWidth + floatRightWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2365 floatLeftWidth = floatRightWidth = 0;
2366 }
2367
2368 if (child->isFloating()) {
2369 if (RenderStyle::usedFloat(*child) == UsedFloat::Left)
2370 floatLeftWidth += w;
2371 else
2372 floatRightWidth += w;
2373 } else
2374 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(w, maxLogicalWidth);
2375
2376 child = child->nextSibling();
2377 }
2378
2379 // Always make sure these values are non-negative.
2380 minLogicalWidth = std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, minLogicalWidth);
2381 maxLogicalWidth = std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, maxLogicalWidth);
2382
2383 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(floatLeftWidth + floatRightWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2384}
2385
2386void RenderBlock::computeChildIntrinsicLogicalWidths(RenderObject& child, LayoutUnit& minPreferredLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxPreferredLogicalWidth) const
2387{
2388 minPreferredLogicalWidth = child.minPreferredLogicalWidth();
2389 maxPreferredLogicalWidth = child.maxPreferredLogicalWidth();
2390}
2391
2392void RenderBlock::computeChildPreferredLogicalWidths(RenderObject& child, LayoutUnit& minPreferredLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxPreferredLogicalWidth) const
2393{
2394 if (child.isBox() && child.isHorizontalWritingMode() != isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
2395 // If the child is an orthogonal flow, child's height determines the width,
2396 // but the height is not available until layout.
2397 // http://dev.w3.org/csswg/css-writing-modes-3/#orthogonal-shrink-to-fit
2398 if (!child.needsLayout()) {
2399 minPreferredLogicalWidth = maxPreferredLogicalWidth = downcast<RenderBox>(child).logicalHeight();
2400 return;
2401 }
2402 auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(child);
2403 if (box.shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio() && box.style().logicalWidth().isFixed()) {
2404 LayoutUnit logicalWidth = LayoutUnit(box.style().logicalWidth().value());
2405 minPreferredLogicalWidth = maxPreferredLogicalWidth = blockSizeFromAspectRatio(box.horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), box.verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), LayoutUnit(box.style().logicalAspectRatio()), box.style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), logicalWidth);
2406 return;
2407 }
2408 minPreferredLogicalWidth = maxPreferredLogicalWidth = box.computeLogicalHeightWithoutLayout();
2409 return;
2410 }
2411
2412 computeChildIntrinsicLogicalWidths(child, minPreferredLogicalWidth, maxPreferredLogicalWidth);
2413
2414 // For non-replaced blocks if the inline size is min|max-content or a definite
2415 // size the min|max-content contribution is that size plus border, padding and
2416 // margin https://drafts.csswg.org/css-sizing/#block-intrinsic
2417 if (child.isRenderBlock()) {
2418 const Length& computedInlineSize = child.style().logicalWidth();
2419 if (computedInlineSize.isMaxContent())
2420 minPreferredLogicalWidth = maxPreferredLogicalWidth;
2421 else if (computedInlineSize.isMinContent())
2422 maxPreferredLogicalWidth = minPreferredLogicalWidth;
2423 }
2424}

2428 if (!element())
2429 return false;
2430
2431 if (element()->isRootEditableElement())
2432 return true;
2433
2434 return false;

2436
2437LayoutUnit RenderBlock::lineHeight(bool firstLine, LineDirectionMode direction, LinePositionMode linePositionMode) const
2438{
2439 // Inline blocks are replaced elements. Otherwise, just pass off to
2440 // the base class. If we're being queried as though we're the root line
2441 // box, then the fact that we're an inline-block is irrelevant, and we behave
2442 // just like a block.
2443 if (isReplaced() && linePositionMode == PositionOnContainingLine)
2444 return RenderBox::lineHeight(firstLine, direction, linePositionMode);
2445
2446 if (firstLine && view().usesFirstLineRules()) {
2447 auto& s = firstLineStyle();
2448 if (&s != &style())
2449 return s.computedLineHeight();
2450 }
2451
2452 return style().computedLineHeight();
2453}
2454
2455LayoutUnit RenderBlock::baselinePosition(FontBaseline baselineType, bool firstLine, LineDirectionMode direction, LinePositionMode linePositionMode) const
2456{
2457 // Inline blocks are replaced elements. Otherwise, just pass off to
2458 // the base class. If we're being queried as though we're the root line
2459 // box, then the fact that we're an inline-block is irrelevant, and we behave
2460 // just like a block.
2461 if (isReplaced() && linePositionMode == PositionOnContainingLine) {
2462 // For "leaf" theme objects, let the theme decide what the baseline position is.
2463 // FIXME: Might be better to have a custom CSS property instead, so that if the theme
2464 // is turned off, checkboxes/radios will still have decent baselines.
2465 // FIXME: Need to patch form controls to deal with vertical lines.
2466 if (style().hasAppearance() && !theme().isControlContainer(style().appearance()))
2467 return theme().baselinePosition(*this);
2468
2469 // CSS2.1 states that the baseline of an inline block is the baseline of the last line box in
2470 // the normal flow. We make an exception for marquees, since their baselines are meaningless
2471 // (the content inside them moves). This matches WinIE as well, which just bottom-aligns them.
2472 // We also give up on finding a baseline if we have a vertical scrollbar, or if we are scrolled
2473 // vertically (e.g., an overflow:hidden block that has had scrollTop moved).
2474 auto ignoreBaseline = [this, direction]() -> bool {
2475 if (isWritingModeRoot() && !isRubyRun())
2476 return true;
2477
2478 auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr;
2479 if (!scrollableArea)
2480 return false;
2481
2482 if (scrollableArea->marquee())
2483 return true;
2484
2485 if (direction == HorizontalLine)
2486 return scrollableArea->verticalScrollbar() || scrollableArea->scrollOffset().y();
2487 return scrollableArea->horizontalScrollbar() || scrollableArea->scrollOffset().x();
2488 };
2489
2490 auto baselinePos = ignoreBaseline() ? std::optional<LayoutUnit>() : inlineBlockBaseline(direction);
2491
2492 if (isDeprecatedFlexibleBox()) {
2493 // Historically, we did this check for all baselines. But we can't
2494 // remove this code from deprecated flexbox, because it effectively
2495 // breaks -webkit-line-clamp, which is used in the wild -- we would
2496 // calculate the baseline as if -webkit-line-clamp wasn't used.
2497 // For simplicity, we use this for all uses of deprecated flexbox.
2498 LayoutUnit bottomOfContent = direction == HorizontalLine ? borderTop() + paddingTop() + contentHeight() : borderRight() + paddingRight() + contentWidth();
2499 if (baselinePos && baselinePos.value() > bottomOfContent)
2500 baselinePos = std::optional<LayoutUnit>();
2501 }
2502 if (baselinePos)
2503 return direction == HorizontalLine ? marginTop() + baselinePos.value() : marginRight() + baselinePos.value();
2504
2505 return RenderBox::baselinePosition(baselineType, firstLine, direction, linePositionMode);
2506 }
2507
2508 const RenderStyle& style = firstLine ? firstLineStyle() : this->style();
2509 const FontMetrics& fontMetrics = style.fontMetrics();
2510 return LayoutUnit { fontMetrics.ascent(baselineType) + (lineHeight(firstLine, direction, linePositionMode) - fontMetrics.height()) / 2 }.toInt();
2511}
2512
2513LayoutUnit RenderBlock::minLineHeightForReplacedRenderer(bool isFirstLine, LayoutUnit replacedHeight) const
2514{
2515 if (!document().inNoQuirksMode() && replacedHeight)
2516 return replacedHeight;
2517
2518 const RenderStyle& style = isFirstLine ? firstLineStyle() : this->style();
2519 if (!(style.lineBoxContain().contains(LineBoxContain::Block)))
2520 return 0;
2521
2522 return std::max<LayoutUnit>(replacedHeight, lineHeight(isFirstLine, isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes));
2523}
2524
2525std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderBlock::firstLineBaseline() const
2526{
2527 if (shouldApplyLayoutContainment(*this))
2528 return std::nullopt;
2529
2530 if (isWritingModeRoot() && !isRubyRun())
2531 return std::optional<LayoutUnit>();
2532
2533 for (RenderBox* curr = firstChildBox(); curr; curr = curr->nextSiblingBox()) {
2534 if (!curr->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
2535 if (auto result = curr->firstLineBaseline())
2536 return LayoutUnit { curr->logicalTop() + result.value() }; // Translate to our coordinate space.
2537 }
2538 }
2539
2540 return std::optional<LayoutUnit>();
2541}
2542
2543std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderBlock::inlineBlockBaseline(LineDirectionMode lineDirection) const
2544{
2545 if (shouldApplyLayoutContainment(*this))
2546 return synthesizedBaselineFromBorderBox(*this, lineDirection) + (lineDirection == HorizontalLine ? marginBottom() : marginLeft());
2547
2548 if (isWritingModeRoot() && !isRubyRun())
2549 return std::optional<LayoutUnit>();
2550
2551 bool haveNormalFlowChild = false;
2552 for (auto* box = lastChildBox(); box; box = box->previousSiblingBox()) {
2553 if (box->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
2554 continue;
2555 haveNormalFlowChild = true;
2556 if (auto result = box->inlineBlockBaseline(lineDirection))
2557 return LayoutUnit { (box->logicalTop() + result.value()).toInt() }; // Translate to our coordinate space.
2558 }
2559
2560 if (!haveNormalFlowChild && hasLineIfEmpty()) {
2561 auto& fontMetrics = firstLineStyle().fontMetrics();
2562 return LayoutUnit { LayoutUnit(fontMetrics.ascent()
2563 + (lineHeight(true, lineDirection, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes) - fontMetrics.height()) / 2
2564 + (lineDirection == HorizontalLine ? borderTop() + paddingTop() : borderRight() + paddingRight())).toInt() };
2565 }
2566
2567 return std::optional<LayoutUnit>();
2568}

2570static inline bool isRenderBlockFlowOrRenderButton(RenderElement& renderElement)
2571{
2572 // We include isRenderButton in this check because buttons are implemented
2573 // using flex box but should still support first-line|first-letter.
2574 // The flex box and specs require that flex box and grid do not support
2575 // first-line|first-letter, though.
2576 // FIXME: Remove when buttons are implemented with align-items instead of
2577 // flex box.
2578 return renderElement.isRenderBlockFlow() || renderElement.isRenderButton();
2579}
2580
2581RenderBlock* RenderBlock::firstLineBlock() const
2582{
2583 RenderBlock* firstLineBlock = const_cast<RenderBlock*>(this);
2584 bool hasPseudo = false;
2585 while (true) {
2586 hasPseudo = firstLineBlock->style().hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine);
2587 if (hasPseudo)
2588 break;
2589 RenderElement* parentBlock = firstLineBlock->parent();
2590 if (firstLineBlock->isReplaced() || firstLineBlock->isFloating()
2591 || !parentBlock || parentBlock->firstChild() != firstLineBlock || !isRenderBlockFlowOrRenderButton(*parentBlock))
2592 break;
2593 firstLineBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(parentBlock);
2594 }
2595
2596 if (!hasPseudo)
2597 return nullptr;
2598
2599 return firstLineBlock;
2600}
2601
2602static inline RenderBlock* findFirstLetterBlock(RenderBlock* start)
2603{
2604 RenderBlock* firstLetterBlock = start;
2605 while (true) {
2606 bool canHaveFirstLetterRenderer = firstLetterBlock->style().hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLetter)
2607 && firstLetterBlock->canHaveGeneratedChildren()
2608 && isRenderBlockFlowOrRenderButton(*firstLetterBlock);
2609 if (canHaveFirstLetterRenderer)
2610 return firstLetterBlock;
2611
2612 RenderElement* parentBlock = firstLetterBlock->parent();
2613 if (firstLetterBlock->isReplaced() || !parentBlock || parentBlock->firstChild() != firstLetterBlock
2614 || !isRenderBlockFlowOrRenderButton(*parentBlock))
2615 return nullptr;
2616 firstLetterBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(parentBlock);
2617 }
2618
2619 return nullptr;
2620}
2621
2622void RenderBlock::getFirstLetter(RenderObject*& firstLetter, RenderElement*& firstLetterContainer, RenderObject* skipObject)
2623{
2624 firstLetter = nullptr;
2625 firstLetterContainer = nullptr;
2626
2627 if (!view().usesFirstLetterRules())
2628 return;
2629
2630 // Don't recur
2631 if (style().styleType() == PseudoId::FirstLetter)
2632 return;
2633
2634 // FIXME: We need to destroy the first-letter object if it is no longer the first child. Need to find
2635 // an efficient way to check for that situation though before implementing anything.
2636 firstLetterContainer = findFirstLetterBlock(this);
2637 if (!firstLetterContainer)
2638 return;
2639
2640 // Drill into inlines looking for our first text descendant.
2641 firstLetter = firstLetterContainer->firstChild();
2642 while (firstLetter) {
2643 if (is<RenderText>(*firstLetter)) {
2644 if (firstLetter == skipObject) {
2645 firstLetter = firstLetter->nextSibling();
2646 continue;
2647 }
2648
2649 break;
2650 }
2651
2652 RenderElement& current = downcast<RenderElement>(*firstLetter);
2653 if (is<RenderListMarker>(current))
2654 firstLetter = current.nextSibling();
2655 else if (current.isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
2656 if (current.style().styleType() == PseudoId::FirstLetter) {
2657 firstLetter = current.firstChild();
2658 break;
2659 }
2660 firstLetter = current.nextSibling();
2661 } else if (current.isReplaced() || is<RenderButton>(current) || is<RenderMenuList>(current))
2662 break;
2663 else if (current.isFlexibleBoxIncludingDeprecated() || current.isRenderGrid())
2664 firstLetter = current.nextSibling();
2665 else if (current.style().hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLetter) && current.canHaveGeneratedChildren()) {
2666 // We found a lower-level node with first-letter, which supersedes the higher-level style
2667 firstLetterContainer = &current;
2668 firstLetter = current.firstChild();
2669 } else
2670 firstLetter = current.firstChild();
2671 }
2672
2673 if (!firstLetter)
2674 firstLetterContainer = nullptr;
2675}

2768void RenderBlock::absoluteRects(Vector<IntRect>& rects, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset) const
2769{
2770 // For blocks inside inlines, we include margins so that we run right up to the inline boxes
2771 // above and below us (thus getting merged with them to form a single irregular shape).
2772 if (auto* continuation = this->continuation()) {
2773 // FIXME: This is wrong for block-flows that are horizontal.
2774 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46781
2775 rects.append(snappedIntRect(accumulatedOffset.x(), accumulatedOffset.y() - collapsedMarginBefore(), width(), height() + collapsedMarginBefore() + collapsedMarginAfter()));
2776 continuation->absoluteRects(rects, accumulatedOffset - toLayoutSize(location() + inlineContinuation()->containingBlock()->location()));
2777 } else
2778 rects.append(snappedIntRect(accumulatedOffset, size()));
2779}

2781void RenderBlock::absoluteQuads(Vector<FloatQuad>& quads, bool* wasFixed) const
2782{
2783 if (!continuation()) {
2784 absoluteQuadsIgnoringContinuation({ { }, size() }, quads, wasFixed);
2785 return;
2786 }
2787 // For blocks inside inlines, we include margins so that we run right up to the inline boxes
2788 // above and below us (thus getting merged with them to form a single irregular shape).
2789 auto logicalRect = FloatRect { 0, -collapsedMarginBefore(), width(), height() + collapsedMarginBefore() + collapsedMarginAfter() };
2790 absoluteQuadsIgnoringContinuation(logicalRect, quads, wasFixed);
2791 collectAbsoluteQuadsForContinuation(quads, wasFixed);
2792}
2793
2794void RenderBlock::absoluteQuadsIgnoringContinuation(const FloatRect& logicalRect, Vector<FloatQuad>& quads, bool* wasFixed) const
2795{
2796 // FIXME: This is wrong for block-flows that are horizontal.
2797 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46781
2798 auto* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2799 if (!fragmentedFlow || !fragmentedFlow->absoluteQuadsForBox(quads, wasFixed, this, logicalRect.y(), logicalRect.maxY()))
2800 quads.append(localToAbsoluteQuad(logicalRect, UseTransforms, wasFixed));
2801}

2832{

2834}
2835
2836void RenderBlock::addFocusRingRects(Vector<LayoutRect>& rects, const LayoutPoint& additionalOffset, const RenderLayerModelObject* paintContainer)
2837{
2838 // For blocks inside inlines, we include margins so that we run right up to the inline boxes
2839 // above and below us (thus getting merged with them to form a single irregular shape).
2840 auto* inlineContinuation = this->inlineContinuation();
2841 if (inlineContinuation) {
2842 // FIXME: This check really isn't accurate.
2843 bool nextInlineHasLineBox = inlineContinuation->firstLineBox();
2844 // FIXME: This is wrong. The principal renderer may not be the continuation preceding this block.
2845 // FIXME: This is wrong for block-flows that are horizontal.
2846 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46781
2847 bool prevInlineHasLineBox = downcast<RenderInline>(*inlineContinuation->element()->renderer()).firstLineBox();
2848 auto topMargin = prevInlineHasLineBox ? collapsedMarginBefore() : 0_lu;
2849 auto bottomMargin = nextInlineHasLineBox ? collapsedMarginAfter() : 0_lu;
2850 LayoutRect rect(additionalOffset.x(), additionalOffset.y() - topMargin, width(), height() + topMargin + bottomMargin);
2851 if (!rect.isEmpty())
2852 rects.append(rect);
2853 } else if (width() && height())
2854 rects.append(LayoutRect(additionalOffset, size()));
2855
2856 if (!hasOverflowClip() && !hasControlClip()) {
2857 if (childrenInline())
2858 addFocusRingRectsForInlineChildren(rects, additionalOffset, paintContainer);
2859
2860 for (auto& box : childrenOfType<RenderBox>(*this)) {
2861 if (is<RenderListMarker>(box))
2862 continue;
2863
2864 FloatPoint pos;
2865 // FIXME: This doesn't work correctly with transforms.
2866 if (box.layer())
2867 pos = box.localToContainerPoint(FloatPoint(), paintContainer);
2868 else
2869 pos = FloatPoint(additionalOffset.x() + box.x(), additionalOffset.y() + box.y());
2870 box.addFocusRingRects(rects, flooredLayoutPoint(pos), paintContainer);
2871 }
2872 }
2873
2874 if (inlineContinuation)
2875 inlineContinuation->addFocusRingRects(rects, flooredLayoutPoint(LayoutPoint(additionalOffset + inlineContinuation->containingBlock()->location() - location())), paintContainer);
2876}

2890
2891LayoutUnit RenderBlock::offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() const
2892{
2893 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
2894 if (layoutState && !layoutState->isPaginated())
2895 return 0;
2896
2897 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2898 if (fragmentedFlow)
2899 return fragmentedFlow->offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment(this);
2900
2901 if (layoutState) {
2902 ASSERT(layoutState->renderer() == this);
2903
2904 LayoutSize offsetDelta = layoutState->layoutOffset() - layoutState->pageOffset();
2905 return isHorizontalWritingMode() ? offsetDelta.height() : offsetDelta.width();
2906 }
2907
2908 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2909 return 0;
2910}
2911
2912RenderFragmentContainer* RenderBlock::fragmentAtBlockOffset(LayoutUnit blockOffset) const
2913{
2914 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2915 if (!fragmentedFlow || !fragmentedFlow->hasValidFragmentInfo())
2916 return 0;
2917
2918 return fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() + blockOffset, true);
2919}
2920
2921static bool canComputeFragmentRangeForBox(const RenderBlock& parentBlock, const RenderBox& childBox, const RenderFragmentedFlow* enclosingFragmentedFlow)
2922{
2923 if (!enclosingFragmentedFlow)
2924 return false;
2925
2926 if (!enclosingFragmentedFlow->hasFragments())
2927 return false;
2928
2929 if (!childBox.canHaveOutsideFragmentRange())
2930 return false;
2931
2932 return enclosingFragmentedFlow->hasCachedFragmentRangeForBox(parentBlock);
2933}
2934
2935bool RenderBlock::childBoxIsUnsplittableForFragmentation(const RenderBox& child) const
2936{
2937 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2938 bool checkColumnBreaks = fragmentedFlow && fragmentedFlow->shouldCheckColumnBreaks();
2939 bool checkPageBreaks = !checkColumnBreaks && view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->pageLogicalHeight();
2940 return child.isUnsplittableForPagination() || child.style().breakInside() == BreakInside::Avoid
2941 || (checkColumnBreaks && child.style().breakInside() == BreakInside::AvoidColumn)
2942 || (checkPageBreaks && child.style().breakInside() == BreakInside::AvoidPage);
2943}
2944
2945void RenderBlock::computeFragmentRangeForBoxChild(const RenderBox& box) const
2946{
2947 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2948 ASSERT(canComputeFragmentRangeForBox(*this, box, fragmentedFlow));
2949
2950 RenderFragmentContainer* startFragment;
2951 RenderFragmentContainer* endFragment;
2952 LayoutUnit offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment = box.offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage();
2953 if (childBoxIsUnsplittableForFragmentation(box))
2954 startFragment = endFragment = fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment, true);
2955 else {
2956 startFragment = fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment, true);
2957 endFragment = fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment + logicalHeightForChild(box), true);
2958 }
2959
2960 fragmentedFlow->setFragmentRangeForBox(box, startFragment, endFragment);
2961}
2962
2963void RenderBlock::estimateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(const RenderBox& box) const
2964{
2965 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2966 if (!canComputeFragmentRangeForBox(*this, box, fragmentedFlow))
2967 return;
2968
2969 if (childBoxIsUnsplittableForFragmentation(box)) {
2970 computeFragmentRangeForBoxChild(box);
2971 return;
2972 }
2973
2974 auto estimatedValues = box.computeLogicalHeight(RenderFragmentedFlow::maxLogicalHeight(), logicalTopForChild(box));
2975 LayoutUnit offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment = box.offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage();
2976 RenderFragmentContainer* startFragment = fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment, true);
2977 RenderFragmentContainer* endFragment = fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstFragment + estimatedValues.m_extent, true);
2978
2979 fragmentedFlow->setFragmentRangeForBox(box, startFragment, endFragment);
2980}
2981
2982bool RenderBlock::updateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(const RenderBox& box) const
2983{
2984 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2985 if (!canComputeFragmentRangeForBox(*this, box, fragmentedFlow))
2986 return false;
2987
2988 RenderFragmentContainer* startFragment = nullptr;
2989 RenderFragmentContainer* endFragment = nullptr;
2990 fragmentedFlow->getFragmentRangeForBox(&box, startFragment, endFragment);
2991
2992 computeFragmentRangeForBoxChild(box);
2993
2994 RenderFragmentContainer* newStartFragment = nullptr;
2995 RenderFragmentContainer* newEndFragment = nullptr;
2996 fragmentedFlow->getFragmentRangeForBox(&box, newStartFragment, newEndFragment);
2997
2998
2999 // Changing the start fragment means we shift everything and a relayout is needed.
3000 if (newStartFragment != startFragment)
3001 return true;
3002
3003 // The fragment range of the box has changed. Some boxes (e.g floats) may have been positioned assuming
3004 // a different range.
3005 if (box.needsLayoutAfterFragmentRangeChange() && newEndFragment != endFragment)
3006 return true;
3007
3008 return false;
3009}
3010
3011LayoutUnit RenderBlock::collapsedMarginBeforeForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
3012{
3013 // If the child has the same directionality as we do, then we can just return its
3014 // collapsed margin.
3015 if (!child.isWritingModeRoot())
3016 return child.collapsedMarginBefore();
3017
3018 // The child has a different directionality. If the child is parallel, then it's just
3019 // flipped relative to us. We can use the collapsed margin for the opposite edge.
3020 if (child.isHorizontalWritingMode() == isHorizontalWritingMode())
3021 return child.collapsedMarginAfter();
3022
3023 // The child is perpendicular to us, which means its margins don't collapse but are on the
3024 // "logical left/right" sides of the child box. We can just return the raw margin in this case.
3025 return marginBeforeForChild(child);
3026}

3029{
3030 // If the child has the same directionality as we do, then we can just return its
3031 // collapsed margin.
3032 if (!child.isWritingModeRoot())
3033 return child.collapsedMarginAfter();
3034
3035 // The child has a different directionality. If the child is parallel, then it's just
3036 // flipped relative to us. We can use the collapsed margin for the opposite edge.
3037 if (child.isHorizontalWritingMode() == isHorizontalWritingMode())
3038 return child.collapsedMarginBefore();
3039
3040 // The child is perpendicular to us, which means its margins don't collapse but are on the
3041 // "logical left/right" side of the child box. We can just return the raw margin in this case.

3046{

3048 // margin quirk.
3049 if (!child.isWritingModeRoot())

3051
3052 // The child has a different directionality. If the child is parallel, then it's just
3053 // flipped relative to us. We can use the opposite edge.

3056
3057 // The child is perpendicular to us and box sides are never quirky in html.css, and we don't really care about
3058 // whether or not authors specified quirky ems, since they're an implementation detail.
3059 return false;

3170
3171std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderBlock::availableLogicalHeightForPercentageComputation() const
3172{
3173 std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableHeight;
3174
3175 // For anonymous blocks that are skipped during percentage height calculation,
3176 // we consider them to have an indefinite height.
3177 if (skipContainingBlockForPercentHeightCalculation(*this, false))
3178 return availableHeight;
3179
3180 const auto& styleToUse = style();
3181
3182 // A positioned element that specified both top/bottom or that specifies
3183 // height should be treated as though it has a height explicitly specified
3184 // that can be used for any percentage computations.
3185 bool isOutOfFlowPositionedWithSpecifiedHeight = isOutOfFlowPositioned() && (!styleToUse.logicalHeight().isAuto() || (!styleToUse.logicalTop().isAuto() && !styleToUse.logicalBottom().isAuto()));
3186
3187 if (isFlexItem() && downcast<RenderFlexibleBox>(parent())->useChildOverridingLogicalHeightForPercentageResolution(*this))
3188 availableHeight = overridingContentLogicalHeight();
3189 else if (isGridItem() && hasOverridingLogicalHeight())
3190 availableHeight = overridingContentLogicalHeight();
3191 else if (styleToUse.logicalHeight().isFixed()) {
3192 LayoutUnit contentBoxHeight = adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing((LayoutUnit)styleToUse.logicalHeight().value());
3193 availableHeight = std::max(0_lu, constrainContentBoxLogicalHeightByMinMax(contentBoxHeight - scrollbarLogicalHeight(), std::nullopt));
3194 } else if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio()) {
3195 availableHeight = blockSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), LayoutUnit(style().logicalAspectRatio()), style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), logicalWidth());
3196 } else if (isOutOfFlowPositionedWithSpecifiedHeight) {
3197 // Don't allow this to affect the block' size() member variable, since this
3198 // can get called while the block is still laying out its kids.
3199 LogicalExtentComputedValues computedValues = computeLogicalHeight(logicalHeight(), 0_lu);
3200 availableHeight = computedValues.m_extent - borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() - scrollbarLogicalHeight();
3201 } else if (styleToUse.logicalHeight().isPercentOrCalculated()) {
3202 std::optional<LayoutUnit> heightWithScrollbar = computePercentageLogicalHeight(styleToUse.logicalHeight());
3203 if (heightWithScrollbar) {
3204 LayoutUnit contentBoxHeightWithScrollbar = adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(heightWithScrollbar.value());
3205 // We need to adjust for min/max height because this method does not
3206 // handle the min/max of the current block, its caller does. So the
3207 // return value from the recursive call will not have been adjusted
3208 // yet.
3209 LayoutUnit contentBoxHeight = constrainContentBoxLogicalHeightByMinMax(contentBoxHeightWithScrollbar - scrollbarLogicalHeight(), std::nullopt);
3210 availableHeight = std::max(0_lu, contentBoxHeight);
3211 }
3212 } else if (isRenderView())
3213 availableHeight = view().pageOrViewLogicalHeight();
3214
3215 return availableHeight;
3216}
3217
3218void RenderBlock::layoutExcludedChildren(bool relayoutChildren)
3219{
3220 if (!isFieldset())
3221 return;
3222
3223 setIntrinsicBorderForFieldset(0);
3224
3225 RenderBox* box = findFieldsetLegend();
3226 if (!box)
3227 return;
3228
3229 box->setIsExcludedFromNormalLayout(true);
3230 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderBox>(*this)) {
3231 if (&child == box || !child.isLegend())
3232 continue;
3233 child.setIsExcludedFromNormalLayout(false);
3234 }
3235
3236 RenderBox& legend = *box;
3237 if (relayoutChildren)
3238 legend.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
3239 legend.layoutIfNeeded();
3240
3241 LayoutUnit logicalLeft;
3242 if (style().isLeftToRightDirection()) {
3243 switch (legend.style().textAlign()) {
3244 case TextAlignMode::Center:
3245 logicalLeft = (logicalWidth() - logicalWidthForChild(legend)) / 2;
3246 break;
3247 case TextAlignMode::Right:
3248 logicalLeft = logicalWidth() - borderEnd() - paddingEnd() - logicalWidthForChild(legend);
3249 break;
3250 default:
3251 logicalLeft = borderStart() + paddingStart() + marginStartForChild(legend);
3252 break;
3253 }
3254 } else {
3255 switch (legend.style().textAlign()) {
3256 case TextAlignMode::Left:
3257 logicalLeft = borderStart() + paddingStart();
3258 break;
3259 case TextAlignMode::Center: {
3260 // Make sure that the extra pixel goes to the end side in RTL (since it went to the end side
3261 // in LTR).
3262 LayoutUnit centeredWidth = logicalWidth() - logicalWidthForChild(legend);
3263 logicalLeft = centeredWidth - centeredWidth / 2;
3264 break;
3265 }
3266 default:
3267 logicalLeft = logicalWidth() - borderStart() - paddingStart() - marginStartForChild(legend) - logicalWidthForChild(legend);
3268 break;
3269 }
3270 }
3271
3272 setLogicalLeftForChild(legend, logicalLeft);
3273
3274 LayoutUnit fieldsetBorderBefore = borderBefore();
3275 LayoutUnit legendLogicalHeight = logicalHeightForChild(legend);
3276 LayoutUnit legendAfterMargin = marginAfterForChild(legend);
3277 LayoutUnit topPositionForLegend = std::max(0_lu, (fieldsetBorderBefore - legendLogicalHeight) / 2);
3278 LayoutUnit bottomPositionForLegend = topPositionForLegend + legendLogicalHeight + legendAfterMargin;
3279
3280 // Place the legend now.
3281 setLogicalTopForChild(legend, topPositionForLegend);
3282
3283 // If the bottom of the legend (including its after margin) is below the fieldset border,
3284 // then we need to add in sufficient intrinsic border to account for this gap.
3285 // FIXME: Should we support the before margin of the legend? Not entirely clear.
3286 // FIXME: Consider dropping support for the after margin of the legend. Not sure other
3287 // browsers support that anyway.
3288 if (bottomPositionForLegend > fieldsetBorderBefore)
3289 setIntrinsicBorderForFieldset(bottomPositionForLegend - fieldsetBorderBefore);
3290
3291 // Now that the legend is included in the border extent, we can set our logical height
3292 // to the borderBefore (which includes the legend and its after margin if they were bigger
3293 // than the actual fieldset border) and then add in our padding before.
3294 setLogicalHeight(borderBefore() + paddingBefore());
3295}

3298{
3299 for (auto& legend : childrenOfType<RenderBox>(*this)) {
3300 if (option == FieldsetIgnoreFloatingOrOutOfFlow && legend.isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
3301 continue;
3302 if (legend.isLegend())
3303 return const_cast<RenderBox*>(&legend);
3304 }
3305 return nullptr;

3404bool RenderBlock::computePreferredWidthsForExcludedChildren(LayoutUnit& minWidth, LayoutUnit& maxWidth) const
3405{
3406 if (!isFieldset())
3407 return false;
3408
3409 auto* legend = findFieldsetLegend();
3410 if (!legend)
3411 return false;
3412
3413 legend->setIsExcludedFromNormalLayout(true);
3414
3415 computeChildPreferredLogicalWidths(*legend, minWidth, maxWidth);
3416
3417 // These are going to be added in later, so we subtract them out to reflect the
3418 // fact that the legend is outside the scrollable area.
3419 auto scrollbarWidth = intrinsicScrollbarLogicalWidth();
3420 minWidth -= scrollbarWidth;
3421 maxWidth -= scrollbarWidth;
3422
3423 const auto& childStyle = legend->style();
3424 auto startMarginLength = childStyle.marginStartUsing(&style());
3425 auto endMarginLength = childStyle.marginEndUsing(&style());
3426 LayoutUnit margin;
3427 LayoutUnit marginStart;
3428 LayoutUnit marginEnd;
3429 if (startMarginLength.isFixed())
3430 marginStart += startMarginLength.value();
3431 if (endMarginLength.isFixed())
3432 marginEnd += endMarginLength.value();
3433 margin = marginStart + marginEnd;
3434
3435 minWidth += margin;
3436 maxWidth += margin;
3437
3438 return true;
3439}

3441LayoutUnit RenderBlock::adjustBorderBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(LayoutUnit height) const
3442{
3443 // FIXME: We're doing this to match other browsers even though it's questionable.
3444 // Shouldn't height:100px mean the fieldset content gets 100px of height even if the
3445 // resulting fieldset becomes much taller because of the legend?
3446 LayoutUnit bordersPlusPadding = borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3447 if (style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::ContentBox)
3448 return height + bordersPlusPadding - intrinsicBorderForFieldset();
3449 return std::max(height, bordersPlusPadding);
3450}

3452LayoutUnit RenderBlock::adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(std::optional<LayoutUnit> height) const
3453{
3454 // FIXME: We're doing this to match other browsers even though it's questionable.
3455 // Shouldn't height:100px mean the fieldset content gets 100px of height even if the
3456 // resulting fieldset becomes much taller because of the legend?
3457 if (!height)
3458 return 0;

3460 if (style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::BorderBox)

3496String RenderBlock::updateSecurityDiscCharacters(const RenderStyle& style, String&& string)
3497{
3498#if !PLATFORM(COCOA)
3499 UNUSED_PARAM(style);
3500 return WTFMove(string);
3501#else
3502 if (style.textSecurity() == TextSecurity::None)
3503 return WTFMove(string);
3504 // This PUA character in the system font is used to render password field dots on Cocoa platforms.
3505 constexpr UChar textSecurityDiscPUACodePoint = 0xF79A;
3506 auto& font = style.fontCascade().primaryFont();
3507 if (!(font.platformData().isSystemFont() && font.glyphForCharacter(textSecurityDiscPUACodePoint)))

3510 // See RenderText::setRenderedText()

3512 constexpr UChar discCharacterToReplace = blackCircle;
3513#else
3514 constexpr UChar discCharacterToReplace = bullet;
3515#endif
3516
